Hi Steve,<br>
<p>
Can you please outline the general Adventist view on creation, prehistory,<br>
prehistoric man and animals, age of the universe and the like? Just curious!<br>
<p>
Thanks,<br>
<p>
Drew Corrigan.<br>
<p>
[The SDA church official stand is that Genesis 1 is literally true and<br>
that the world was created in six literal days a few thousand years ago.<br>
 Those who believe otherwise have learned to keep their mouth shut. <br>
There are some hints in early Ellen G. White writings of where so-called<br>
apemen fossils may have originated, but no article of faith on this. <br>
The universe is thought to be much older because of our belief that<br>
intelligent life exists elsewhere in it.  <br>
<p>
Evolution is officially a taboo topic on SDAnet because of various flame<br>
wars which occured during the unmoderated Merger period.  But since that<br>
time, evolution-related topics have come up and nobody has dared to<br>
touch them, such as the time when people asked if evolution was taught<br>
at Andrews University and none of the ten Andrews faculty on this list<br>
dared say a word.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
