<!-- body="start" -->
Jesus said the Holy Spirit would witness of him.  See John 15:26-27.  The<br>
Holy Spirit could hardly be expected to say something different fromwhat<br>
Jesus and the Father--and therefore the Scriptures--already said.<br>
<p>
One would imagine that if the content of the message is different, the<br>
origin is also different.  But to be able to argue that, one needs to<br>
be clear on the inspiration and authority of the Bible.<br>
<p>
Nancy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
