<title>Jul_1992: Re: Evolution at Andrews University</title>
<h1>Re: Evolution at Andrews University</h1>
Daniel R. Bidwell (<i>bidwell@elrond.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 2 Jul 92 7:37:46 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#9">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#9">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#9">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#9">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0010.html">McCluskey G: "Re: right to life"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0008.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Holy Spirit and Conscience"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0007.html">Drew Corrigan: "Re: "Discovered--Noah's Ark""</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; [The SDA church official stand is that Genesis 1 is literally true and</i><br>
<i>&gt; ... </i><br>
<i>&gt; Evolution is officially a taboo topic on SDAnet because of various flame</i><br>
<i>&gt; wars which occured during the unmoderated Merger period.  But since that</i><br>
<i>&gt; time, evolution-related topics have come up and nobody has dared to</i><br>
<i>&gt; touch them, such as the time when people asked if evolution was taught</i><br>
<i>&gt; at Andrews University and none of the ten Andrews faculty on this list</i><br>
<i>&gt; dared say a word.  SCT]</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
I do not believe that the reason that none of the 10 Andrews faculty on<br>
this list did not respond to the question of evolution being taught at<br>
Andrews was because that we didn't dare to.  As a member of the Computer<br>
Science department, I know that it is not being taught in our<br>
department. -:)  I suspect that the others haven't responded for the<br>
same reasons that I haven't and that is that I have been teaching an<br>
overload and haven't had the time.<br>
<p>
I have not had close contact with the Biology department, but from the<br>
discussions that I have been in, I do not believe that evolution as a<br>
source of major development (macro evolution) is taught there.<br>
<p>
As a lay person just like anyone else, I believe that there may be<br>
evidence for micro evolution, small changes occuring due to cross<br>
breeding, mutation, etc.  I believe that evidence to support this can be<br>
found around any dairy farm, or horse stables.  I certainly see evidence<br>
of it in the local TV commercials for different varieties of corn that<br>
are good for this or that.<br>
<p>
Everyone can flame away at this, I am leaving for a three week vacation<br>
with my family and will have a great time reguardless of what is said.<br>
-:)<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Daniel R. Bidwell	|	bidwell@andrews.edu
Andrews University	Computer Science &amp; Information Systems Department
If two always agree, one of them is unnecesary
</pre>
