The subject of Noah's Ark has been a hobby of mine since 1974.  And I am<br>
currently in the process of organizing Ark-athon II,  a Noah's Ark<br>
convention.  This will be a time with many of those who are or have been<br>
involved with the search for the Ark can meet together exchange stories<br>
and share expirences.  One of the main purposes of the meeting is to debunk<br>
the claims of Ron Wyatt, David Fasold and others who claim that the<br>
durunipar geologic formation is the Ark.<br>
<p>
No, SDA's are not the only ones fooled by such nonsense.  I hear from several<br>
of the other researchers that people from all Christian walks have been<br>
misled by these people.<br>
<p>
If it all works out, Ark-athon II will be held in January, 93 here in <br>
Portland, Oregon.  I'll fill you in as things become more definate.<br>
<p>
Allen Roy<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
