Yes Randall, there are other Libertarian SDAs.  My husband and I have<br>
both been members of the national party, although the last two states<br>
we have lived in (OK and KY) are vehemently 2-party states.  My whole<br>
family in California has been Libertarian for years, and my Dad and<br>
brother were even delegates to the state convention in the 80s.  To me,<br>
it is the position that makes the most sense from a Christian viewpoint.<br>
Christ was one of the least coercive leaders in history, and God values<br>
our freedom of choice over our salvation!  As one of our pastors said<br>
our God-given power to love others too often turns into the love of<br>
power over others, thus all the attempts to legislate people's private<br>
lives...<br>
 <br>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
