<!-- body="start" -->
A question from an "outsider" :-),<br>
<p>
Who is A. C. McClure? How are the Adventists organised and governed?<br>
<p>
Thanks,<br>
<p>
Drew Corrigan.<br>
[A.C. McClure is the president of the North American Division <br>
of Seventh-day Adventists.  He, along with eleven other division presidents<br>
around the world, is responsible to the General Conference and appointed by <br>
it, there is also an overall president and five general vice-presidents.<br>
The General Conference leadership is picked by the full session which meets<br>
every five years and whose delegates are chosen by the union conferences,<br>
which correspond roughly to international boundaries around the world, <br>
except for large places such as India, USA, Australia which are chopped into <br>
more than one union.  Within the unions there are conferences and fields.<br>
A 20-page document condensed into 8 lines.  SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0024.html">Danny Kumamoto: "accepting creationism?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0022.html">Steven Timm: "Re: "Discovered--Noah's Ark""</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0015.html">Steven Timm: "Special day of prayer"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
