<title>Jul_1992: He's heeerrrrreeeee!!!!!!!!</title>
<h1>He's heeerrrrreeeee!!!!!!!!</h1>
McCluskey G (<i>COTRSSM@sea04vm.navsea.navy.mil</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 13 Jul 92 12:52:34 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#31">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#31">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#31">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#31">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0032.html">malcolm butler: "Re: service jobs and the Sabbath"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0030.html">McCluskey G: "service jobs and the Sabbath"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
  Scott and Linda Mattes are pleased to announce the arrival of their<br>
son, David Scott, on 7/13/92.  David showed up at 0645EDT after giving<br>
his mother just about 3 hours of grief (labor).  Measuring 22" and 10lb<br>
3.5oz (really, not bad, we were expecting 11-12lb), David has large<br>
hands and feet and medium brown hair.  Sisters Toni (7), Carolyn (3) and<br>
Lindsay (1) are pleased as punch that bother finally showed up.  Mom is<br>
doing well and is very pleased that the month and a half of daily labor<br>
pains are over with.<br>
<p>
  Watch this space for further additions, say in 2-3 years.<br>
<p>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<br>
