<title>Jul_1992: Re: Until it's someone you know...</title>
<h1>Re: Until it's someone you know...</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 14 Jul 92 12:01:52 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#36">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#36">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#36">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#36">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0037.html">Joanne Figueiredo: "RE: Until it's someone you know..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0035.html">Stan Macasieb: "Re: Until it's someone you know..."</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0033.html">Steven Timm: "Until it's someone you know..."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0049.html">moynihan_r@apollo.hp.com: "Re: Until it's someone you know..."</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[Steven Timm writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; And though I could pound the keyboard for hours about the </i><br>
<i>&gt; gay rights lobby that wants to pervert the morals of our children, this</i><br>
<i>&gt; won't help my friends.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; What does the SDA church have to say to homosexuals today?  (not AT, _TO_)</i><br>
<i>&gt; What will it take to develop an approach which emphasizes Bible morality</i><br>
<i>&gt; and relationship theology, not fear-mongering and insults?</i><br>
<p>
This is probably not exhaustive, but I reckon there are two basic reasons<br>
for homosexuality - being persuaded by Satan's sophistries (in all its forms)<br>
because we are not wise in God's ways and words (Jer 50:6; Ps 119:11), and<br>
outright rebellion against God's order and against His design for our bodies.<br>
[Interestingly, those are sort of the basics that underly the transgressions<br>
of each and every one of us (Isa 53:6).  Morris Venden has an apt sermon<br>
title:  "God Says, But I Think".]<br>
<p>
A heart in rebellion is not open to being taught of the Lord (Jam 4:6,<br>
1Pet 5:5, Prov 14:9); the heart that is humble is teachable (Ps 25, also<br>
other refs in Psalms &amp; Proverbs).  Getting it that way can come from<br>
recognizing God's goodness and mercy (Rom 2:4).<br>
<p>
For your friend?  Comfort (1 Pet 5:7).  Assurance (Rom 5:8).  Basic stuff<br>
on God's unconditional acceptance of us to save us.  Scripture is full<br>
of examples of people who really blew it, yet God's love for them was<br>
unrequited (cf. David, King Manasseh).  Then, move on to Lordship.  Romans 5<br>
&amp; 6 and Colossians 2 &amp; 3 are basic.  One needs to want to discover and follow<br>
God's purposes (cf. Phi 2:13), which desire God promises to give to us.<br>
Grace is the desire and the power to do His will.  Grace is the indwelling<br>
Holy Spirit (Rev 3:20).<br>
<p>
Establish the basics and let the Holy Spirit prepare the heart and present<br>
openings for specifics on God's best (going from milk to meat, Heb 5, 1Pet 2).<br>
Rejoice in that both inherited and cultivated sinful tendencies can be<br>
and are to be overcome (2Cor 12:9; Rev 21:7 and others in Revelation as well<br>
as elsewhere in the NT).<br>
<p>
We were not born male or female by chance; God made us that way (Gen 1:27, 5:2;<br>
Ps 139:14-16).  As surely as His power sustains the universe, He sustains us<br>
from the moment of conception (Acts 17:28); indeed, we were custom designed<br>
(Ps 139:16).  Babies just do not "happen" (cf. Gen 29:31, et al).  Is it His<br>
design for any to have homosexual tendencies?  I say No (cf. Rom 1).  We may<br>
because of our race's fallen condition (Ex 20:5b), but God has a solution<br>
(Ex 20:6; 1Jn 1:9, 2Pet 3:18))<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  On Attitude &amp; the Immune System:  A sound heart is the life of the flesh:
    but envy the rottenness of the bones.  Prov 14:30
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
