<!-- body="start" -->
the general Adventist view on creation, prehistory, etc...<br>
<p>
[The SDA church official stand is that Genesis 1 is literally true and<br>
that the world was created in six literal days a few thousand years ago.<br>
The universe is thought to be much older because of our belief that<br>
intelligent life exists elsewhere in it.  SCT]<br>
<p>
[I ask]<br>
(Q1)  Are you, then, limiting the heaven and the earth of Genesis 1:1 <br>
to the planet Earth and its atmosphere?  What about the creation of <br>
the stars in Gen. 1:14?<br>
<p>
(Q2)  With all due respect, I thought the idea of extraterrestrial <br>
life was limited to those who got their information from the <br>
[blank] or the [blank].  [Original, unkind words deleted due to the<br>
prompting of the H.S.--DEB]  Is this truly a generally held SDA <br>
view?<br>
<p>
(Q3)  Accepting ET life for the sake of argument :), how does that <br>
presuppose an ancient universe?<br>
