The following is part of today's daily stock quotes and news<br>
clips that I daily receive internally here at work. This especially<br>
caught my attention, particularly the last statement about Jesus. <br>
Anyone have more information about it? <br>
<p>
"Clinton was on VISN (a religious network) this weekend to talk about<br>
family values but it rapidly degenerated into a discussion of<br>
establishment religion.  Clinton was asked how he could be for<br>
capital punishment if the Bible taught respect for human life, for<br>
example.  He said that it had been hard to let four people be<br>
executed while he was governor, but not much more.  No one has the<br>
courage to ask how one can justify war but that would probably be impolite.<br>
He was also asked about the Supreme Court decision on prayer at<br>
public assemblies at schools.  This was done where Clinton went<br>
to school but he agreed that the separation of church and state<br>
probably required this decision.  On the other hand, since Jesus told<br>
his disciples never to pray in public and roundly critised anyone<br>
that prayed out loud, maybe the Supreme Court did establish religion."<br>
<p>
<p>
God bless, Joanne Figueiredo<br>
