<title>Jul_1992: Race Relations: a correction</title>
<h1>Race Relations: a correction</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 22 Jul 1992 17:12:03 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#60">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#60">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#60">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#60">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0061.html">Steven Timm: "Some random thoughts on homosexuality"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0059.html">Joanne Figueiredo: "Correction"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some time ago I commented on SDAnet that there was irony in the fact<br>
that those North Americans who strongly favor racial unity in South <br>
African churches are the same ones who support separate conferences<br>
and unions for Blacks in North America.<br>
<p>
I have since read the Spectrum article describing that meeting, and<br>
what I have called a fact is not a fact at all.  In fact, Calvin Rock,<br>
African-American VP of the church, who chaired the meeting, was one of <br>
the major voices urging caution and not forcing the unions and conferences<br>
of S. Africa to integrate before they were ready.<br>
<p>
I apologize for my error and the storm it caused, causing one member to <br>
leave the list.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
