<title>Jul_1992: homosexuality/SDA</title>
<h1>homosexuality/SDA</h1>
Lola (<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>23 Jul 1992 10:33:52 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#62">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#62">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#62">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#62">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0063.html">Steven Timm: "Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0061.html">Steven Timm: "Some random thoughts on homosexuality"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0063.html">Steven Timm: "Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I think it is imperative to separate the issue of promiscuity from that<br>
of sexual orientation.  I know plenty of heterosexuals who proposition<br>
their friends -- this is NOT a phenomenon limited to homosexuals!<br>
Promiscuity is condemned no matter what your orientation, I believe<br>
we could all agree on that point.<br>
<p>
Now, as for genetic basis for homosexuality.  What if it IS genetically<br>
based, not like mental retardation or alcoholism, but more like being<br>
left-handed?  Do we cure lefties?  We used to try and it caused no end<br>
of trouble for the poor kids.  What would be the attitude of the church<br>
then?  I think I can predict that there would be a major split with one<br>
side claiming that all the condemnation of homosexuality in the Bible<br>
still applied even to loving monogamous relationships, and the other side<br>
saying that a lot of the Biblical injunctions were culturally based and<br>
would not apply to homosexual marriage.<br>
<p>
Personally, I'm suspending judgement, as we are all enjoined to do anyway!<br>
I have had gay friends who were indeed in traumatic circumstances because<br>
of their feelings of guilt and fear of what the church would say should<br>
they live with someone of the same gender.  They were in no way "wicked"<br>
people, in the way that some of my heterosexual but predatory acquaintances<br>
seem to me to be "wicked."  But there iI go, judging the heterosexuals!<br>
It's a hard habit to break...<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
