<title>Jul_1992: Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)</title>
<h1>Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)</h1>
Bob Moynihan (<i>moynihan_r@apollo.hp.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 24 Jul 92 09:11:03 EDT </i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#66">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#66">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#66">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#66">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0067.html">Mark T Brower: "Re: Towards a theology of the human body"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0065.html">Gross: "Judging"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Timm writes:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; The key difference between then and now is that at that time the church</i><br>
<i>&gt; authorities were under the clear, present, and daily guidance of the</i><br>
<i>&gt; Holy Spirit.  Only under this influence can we hope to judge fairly.</i><br>
                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ <br>
<i>&gt; But once given this power, judge we can and judge we must.</i><br>
<p>
*** Note: The 'you' below is -not- intended as the personal 'you' of <br>
    Steve Timm, rather it is the generic 'you'.       -Bob<br>
<p>
Problem is, people judge others whether or not the Holy Spirit is guiding<br>
them.  Judging behavior is one thing.  Judging -people- is something else.<br>
Usually, it is a simple matter to judge the actions of another to be wrong.<br>
However, judging the inherent worth and/or righteousness of the wrongdoer<br>
is something else entirely.  If you accept that you are a sinful person, <br>
that you have your own failings in the eyes of the Lord, then you have -no-<br>
right -whatsoever- to judge another person as unrighteous.  What makes <br>
your sins of less import than theirs?  What makes you more righteous than<br>
them?  Perhaps they are looking at you and, seeing your sins, judging you<br>
as well.<br>
<p>
Paul wrote that it was okay to judge.  -Jesus- said not to.  Given that<br>
apparent conflict, it is easy for me to decide whose words to follow. <br>
<p>
-Bob                              Disclaimer: I speak only for myself<br>
 moynihan_r@apollo.hp.com         <br>
