<title>Jul_1992: Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)</title>
<h1>Re: homosexuality/SDA  (Judging)</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>24 Jul 92 10:53:29 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#68">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#68">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#68">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#68">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0069.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Towards a theology of the human body"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0067.html">Mark T Brower: "Re: Towards a theology of the human body"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve, Amen to all of your comments on judging. I feel that this is a good<br>
time to redeem myself! In the past I have probably given some the idea<br>
that I am totally against all rules and regulations. I really am not! I do<br>
not like to see Christian people put 100% of their focus on rules. By so<br>
doing we lock ourselves in and cannot be free in Jesus Christ. EGW<br>
referring to schools gives us the idea that rules should be few and well<br>
thought out. In our Jr. Academy close by in my area for this coming year<br>
we have deleted all rules on dress code and established one statement as<br>
far as dress is concerned.<br>
<p>
One case in point, a couple who live in our area recently had a new born.<br>
The husband is a former SDA, and his parents are members of our church.<br>
His wife has a catholic background. I have explained to them about Child<br>
dedication and the responsibility of Christian parents in training the<br>
child. The couple wanted to know if it was alright for the Head Elder to<br>
do the dedication service since the wife had worked for him in the past. I<br>
readily gave my approval. When contacted the head elder refused without<br>
giving them any explanation. Because they are not church members he<br>
doesn't feel that it is proper. He has a right to his views. I will be<br>
dedicating the child tomorrow at church. I believe that is an example of<br>
what can happy when we focus completely on rules.<br>
<p>
The example in the Ministry magazine a few months back is proper at this<br>
point. In a framed picture of Christ, Christ is the focal point the frame<br>
is the doctrines!<br>
<p>
It would appear to me, Steve, that the bottom line of this "thread" is:<br>
SIN IS SIN WHEREVER WE FIND IT. It seems to be less sin if we have the<br>
problem. It is really sin if that sin is not a problem with us.<br>
<p>
A good share of us if not all of us have tendencies to certain sins. On a<br>
very hot day some times I get the thought of how good would a cold glass<br>
of beer taste?!! I quickly dismiss it and think that I overcame that 39<br>
years ago and I certainly do not want to mess my life up with that sort<br>
of thing when I have learned to live without it.<br>
<p>
any comments anybody??<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
