Steve, Appreciated your thoughts on health. The lifestyle that I live<br>
comes from the idea that I want to live to be 100 years old if time lasts<br>
and I want to be in the very best of health. If I can glorify Jesus Christ<br>
in the process I am happy. I want to have a clear mind and be able to<br>
discern spiritual things.<br>
<p>
We used to at Michigan Campmeeting purchase $200.00 worth of what we used<br>
to call "health foods." My wife and I have both lowered our cholesterol<br>
when we gave them up! We discovered for ourselves that eating meat was<br>
almost more healthy than eating the so called analogs. Occasionally we do<br>
eat a choplet or a hot dog when our grandchildren are over for a visit.<br>
But, usually never keep them in the house.<br>
<p>
Sadly but true, the SDA church has lost it as far as health is concerned<br>
in my humble opinion. I have more confidence in Dr. Gabe Merkin of<br>
Washington, DC's WRC radio talk show, and / or Dr. McDougall. SDAs are<br>
seemingly getting on the bandwagon now that the world is promoting<br>
healthful living. <br>
<p>
I have lost 31 pounds since Sept. of last year and have about the same<br>
amount again to go and I give all the glory to fruits, vegetables, beans,<br>
whole grains, etc.<br>
<p>
I very rarely eat cheese except the kind made with 100% skim milk, very<br>
rarely eat an egg, ( we use egg beaters ) and drink skim or 1% milk. I<br>
want to continue to have a healthy body because that is what God designed<br>
and wants me to have.  (3John v.2) My reasons for living healthy do not<br>
stem from having a "guilt trip" via the SDA church. My focus is what God<br>
says in his word. I take full responsibility for my obesity but it was<br>
listening to the so called health reformists in the church that I found<br>
my self 61 years old and almost a health hazard. Please do not give me<br>
the report that Adventists live longer -- let's do another report and see<br>
what the data really is! I will be eternally grateful for Dr. Merkin here<br>
in the DC area and Dr. McDougall (non SDA) at our hospital in Calif.<br>
(forgot name of SDA hosp. where McDougall is now). I believe Weimar<br>
Institute has done a lot for SDAs to get on track health wise. I would not<br>
mind going out there to get my weight under control but can't afford it.<br>
<p>
Steve, I am not a health fanatic. My lifestyle is good for me and I do not<br>
try to force it on other people.  <br>
<p>
Take care Steve, appreciate your insights.<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
