<title>Jul_1992: Sexual Ethics in the Adventist Ministry</title>
<h1>Sexual Ethics in the Adventist Ministry</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 29 Jul 1992 16:02:43 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#72">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#72">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#72">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#72">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0073.html">Alice Fay Martin: "thanx/ dating/ marriage"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0071.html">Steven Timm: "More theology of the body"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
This is some information taken from a position paper presented by Len <br>
McMillan at the meeting of the Association Of Adventist Family Life <br>
Professionals at Andrews University this month.<br>
<p>
According to Christianity Today, the percentage of clergy at large<br>
who admitted to some sexually inappropriate activity is 25%.  One<br>
out of eight admit to having commited adultery.<br>
<p>
A group of 586 respondents who answered McMillan's questionnaire at his <br>
seminar for pastors and associated caregivers gave some interesting <br>
pictures of the Adventist community.<br>
<p>
50% of males and 47% of the females in this group had engaged in<br>
premarital sex.  Those who had grown up in Adventist homes had<br>
significantly less<br>
p[ercentage than this.<br>
<p>
11% of males and 10% of females had had sex with someone other than<br>
their spouse than since marriage [note this does not imply they were<br>
necessarily in the ministry at that time.]  For those that grew up in<br>
Adventist homes<br>
the percentage is 12%.<br>
<p>
65% of males and 31% of females admitted to being sexually attracted to<br>
a parishoner or student without actually engaging in sex.<br>
 <br>
47% would not feel comfortable talking to their spouse about such an<br>
attraction.<br>
<p>
10% of pastors admitted to having an affair.  16% of the females at <br>
the event, which included pastors wives, teachers, and counselors,<br>
admitted to an affair.<br>
<p>
6% of the males and 19% of the females said they were sexually abused <br>
as children.  Among those from Adventist homes male and female,<br>
the figure was 8% as opposed to 18% from non-religious homes.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
