<!-- body="start" -->
Since I never post but read SDAnet regularly... I thought I'd just <br>
write and say thanks to Steve for his efforts as moderater as well as <br>
acknowledge his ability to foster stimulating discussion on topics of <br>
interest and importance.... Thanx!<br>
<p>
Of recent interest to me I have a couple of questions for those with <br>
some further insight. <br>
<p>
Recently an SDA friend of mine met, became engaged and married <br>
within 8 months.  There are a number of things about this union <br>
which concern me besides the shortness of the courtship but the one <br>
which troubles me most is her decision to marry outside her faith, <br>
not just outside SDA but outside Christianity to a converted <br>
practicing Moslem.<br>
<p>
So here are my questions related to this topic:<br>
<p>
How does the church relate to a young adult who chooses to date <br>
someone outside their particular church faith (i.e. non-SDA)?  What <br>
principles are there to guide the individual and the church in relating <br>
to that individual?<br>
<p>
Was it Biblically wrong for my friend to marry a non-Christian?  Is <br>
she lost in some way by her decision?  If so how does the church <br>
relate to her now?  (Needless to say, a once regular member, she has <br>
not returned to church since the wedding, embittered by the peoples <br>
and pastoral response.)<br>
<p>
-Alice<br>
armg9488@uxa.cso.uiuc.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
