<title>Jul_1992: Marriage outside the faith</title>
<h1>Marriage outside the faith</h1>
Dan Blake (<i>dblake@hprnd.rose.hp.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 30 Jul 92 23:12:46 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#74">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#74">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#74">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#74">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0073.html">Alice Fay Martin: "thanx/ dating/ marriage"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; Alice writes:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; which troubles me most is her decision to marry outside her faith, </i><br>
<i>&gt; not just outside SDA but outside Christianity to a converted </i><br>
<i>&gt; practicing Moslem.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Was it Biblically wrong for my friend to marry a non-Christian?</i><br>
<p>
Absolutely.  1Kings 11:1-11; 2Cor. 6:14-18.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Is she lost in some way by her decision?</i><br>
<p>
I take the minority position that one can not lose his salvation<br>
(Rom. 8:35-39).  However, I think her decision says rather<br>
loudly that she is not saved.  How can you choose an earthly<br>
lord who denies the deity of your heavenly Lord?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; If so how does the church relate to her now?</i><br>
<p>
This is very difficult.  Paul asks, "What will ye?  Shall I come<br>
unto you with a rod or in love and a spirit of gentleness?"<br>
(1Cor. 4:21)  Those in Corinth had to choose; so did your friend.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; (Needless to say, a once regular member, she has </i><br>
<i>&gt; not returned to church since the wedding, embittered by the peoples </i><br>
<i>&gt; and pastoral response.)</i><br>
<p>
It is, indeed, sad when a disciple turns back and no more walks<br>
with Jesus.  I believe this is a matter of a leopard showing its<br>
true spots.  I recommend you John 6:59-66, especially verse 64.<br>
Whereas we can judge only by a person's walk, God is not so limited.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; -Alice</i><br>
<p>
Nice to hear from you Alice.<br>
<p>
-Dan Blake<br>
dblake@hprnd.rose.hp.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
