<title>Jun_1992: Anger</title>
<h1>Anger</h1>
Eric Snyder (<i>ESNYDER%PSUHMC.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 3 Jun 92 15:58 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#9">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#9">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#9">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#9">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0010.html">Fred Christiansen: "A curious reference to SDA's"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0008.html">Rolaant: "Seeking Advice on Trapped Emotions"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;        There is a good friend of mine here who is having</i><br>
<i>&gt;    trouble with anger.  He apparently does not express it but</i><br>
<i>&gt;    keeps it inside.  He has talked to me about this, and</i><br>
<i>&gt;    expresses the fear that he may sometime lose control over</i><br>
<i>&gt;    his stored anger.  In that event he might do just about</i><br>
<i>&gt;    anything.  He has asked me for advice on how he can release</i><br>
<i>&gt;    it safely, without hurting anyone or anything.  I have</i><br>
<i>&gt;    suggested physical exercise, but this is apparently not</i><br>
<i>&gt;    enough.  I am no expert in situations such as this, so I</i><br>
<i>&gt;    seek helpful advice from anyone who may have wisdom to</i><br>
<i>&gt;    share.</i><br>
 <br>
     I would never want to suggest that there is a 2 minute answer<br>
   to this problem.  You may want to find out what the source of<br>
   the anger is.  It sounds like this person needs to talk their<br>
   anger out.  Perhaps meet with a professional counselor.  But I<br>
   would exersize caution if seeking a counselor.  If its the wrong<br>
   type of counselor, it may even backfire.  Perhaps you may want to<br>
   explain to this person that by allowing the anger to build, they<br>
   put themselves in jeopardy.  You may want to find out if this<br>
   person is harboring bitterness.  If so, they need to be freed from<br>
   it to experience joy in the Lord.<br>
   My little 2c<br>
   Eric<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
