<title>Jun_1992: day of crucifixion</title>
<h1>day of crucifixion</h1>
Tim Swensen (<i>swensen@ecn.purdue.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 1 Jun 92 12:40:13 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#3">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#3">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#3">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#3">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0004.html">Scott Mattes: "Passing something along to you"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0002.html">Ben Clausen: "mother's pride"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDAnetters,<br>
<p>
Samuele Bacchiocchi has written a book which may help clear up the issue of<br>
which day of the week Christ was crucified and which day he arose from the <br>
tomb.  I quote from the back cover of the book:<br>
<p>
<i>     &gt; In "The Time of the Crucifixion and the Resurrection" Dr. Samuele </i><br>
<i>     &gt; Bacchiocchi examines at great length each of three crucial texts </i><br>
<i>     &gt; adduced in support of the Wednesday Crucifixion dating....</i><br>
<i>     &gt;</i><br>
<i>     &gt; The book has been written in a clear, non-technical style with the </i><br>
<i>     &gt; earnest desire to help Christians appreciate more fully not merely</i><br>
<i>     &gt; the time element of Christ's death, but primarily the full scope of </i><br>
<i>     &gt; Christ's redemptive ministry, which includes His earthly atonement,</i><br>
<i>     &gt; heavenly ministry and final restoration at His second Advent.</i><br>
<p>
It is available for $12.95 postpaid from:<br>
     BIBLICAL PERSPECTIVES<br>
     4569 Lisa Lane<br>
     Berrien Springs, MI 49103<br>
<p>
I hope this helps.<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
swensen@ecn.purdue.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
