<!-- body="start" -->
  I typed this in thinking you might find it interesting and/or give you<br>
ideas.  Typos are mine.<br>
<p>
  This is directed at the USofA, but it could easily apply to any<br>
country that allows their citizens a voice in government.<br>
<p>
<p>
---------------------------------8&lt;-----------------------------<br>
   Fellow citizens, When this country was founded it was to be 'of, for and by<br>
the people'.  Now it seems to be a government of, for and by special interest<br>
groups.  Why?  Because we the people have become less and less involved in the<br>
day to day workings of our government and put complete trust in politicans to do<br>
what is good for us.  The politicans then listen to those who give them input<br>
and we the people haven't been doing much of that, but the special interest<br>
groups have.<br>
   How can we get back the control of our government from the special interest<br>
groups?  Let your elected servants know what you think on the issues and make<br>
your choices stick with your vote!  Less than half of the eligible people in<br>
America are registered voters and less than half of them don't vote.<br>
   A good way to make your feelings known is the letter.  .....................<br>
...... SOME STUFF DELETED .....................................................<br>
..................................................  Then fill in and send copie<br>
of this letter to your government servants.  At 5 cents a copy at your local<br>
library your total cost would be under $5.  The library or phone book is a good<br>
place to get the addresses you will need for mailing. or call the U.S.  Capital<br>
Switch Board at (202) 224-3121.<br>
   Let the President, congress, your governor and state representatives, your<br>
mayor and city council people know how you feel about the issues.  Check below<br>
whether you are For, Against or Undecided about these issues.  If you don't care<br>
about one then leave it blank.<br>
                                                                     EoZ<br>
MY elected government servant,<br>
<p>
   Below I have indicated some of the subjects that I am concerned about and how<br>
I feel about them.  I expect that you will take into consideration my position<br>
about these topics when performing your duties, especially as this is an<br>
election year.<br>
<p>
F/A/U                                   F/A/U<br>
_ _ _ Abortion                          _ _ _ Freedom of the press<br>
_ _ _ Abortion, federally funded        _ _ _ Gun control<br>
_ _ _ Abortion, fetus sex/imperfection  _ _ _ Gun control, banning automatics<br>
_ _ _ Abortion, state funded            _ _ _ Gun control, banning certain type<br>
_ _ _ Abortion, threaten life of mother _ _ _ Gun control, waiting period<br>
_ _ _ Accountibility of businesses      _ _ _ Helping homeless<br>
_ _ _ Accountibility of citizens        _ _ _ I.R.S. court<br>
_ _ _ Accountibility of gov officials   _ _ _ Mistrials due to technicalities<br>
_ _ _ Accountibility of the press       _ _ _ National health care insurance<br>
_ _ _ Budget, balanced                  _ _ _ Political action committes (PACs)<br>
_ _ _ Budget, honest and realistic      _ _ _ Pollution<br>
_ _ _ Campaign contributions            _ _ _ Pork barrel projects<br>
_ _ _ Death penality, drug pushing      _ _ _ Pornography<br>
_ _ _ Death penality, drug smuggling    _ _ _ Schools, private/home<br>
_ _ _ Death penality, drunk driving     _ _ _ Schools, public<br>
_ _ _ Death penality, murder            _ _ _ Speeding<br>
_ _ _ Death penality, repeat offenders  _ _ _ Subsidies, business<br>
_ _ _ Drunk driving                     _ _ _ Subsidies, education<br>
_ _ _ Fetal (aborted) tissue research   _ _ _ Subsidies, food<br>
_ _ _ Fetal tissue research             _ _ _ Subsidies, grazing land<br>
_ _ _ First amendment rights            _ _ _ Subsidies, irrigation<br>
_ _ _ Food labeling                     _ _ _ Subsidies, timber<br>
_ _ _ Food purity                       _ _ _ Subsidies, tobacco<br>
_ _ _ Foreign aid, humanitarian         _ _ _ Taxes, equalness of<br>
_ _ _ Foreign aid, military             _ _ _ Washington D.C., statehood<br>
_ _ _ Foreign intervention by U.S.      _ _ _ Welfare programs, federal<br>
_ _ _ Foreign meddling with our laws    _ _ _ Welfare programs, local<br>
_ _ _ Foreign trips by gov officials    _ _ _ Welfare programs, state<br>
_ _ _ Freedom of religion               _ _ _ Women in combat<br>
<p>
                                       Signed,<br>
Scott       | No success can compensate for failure in the home. David O. McKay<br>
Mattes      | President 1951-70, Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<br>
