To Whom It May Concern:<br>
 <br>
I am currently a graduate student at the University of Michigan pursuing<br>
a masters degree in information and library studies. I have about one more<br>
year to go before completingmy degree requirements, so I thought this would<br>
be a good time to start exploring employment opportunities around the<br>
country or abroad. The Lord has given me the opportunity to return to school,<br>
in spite of the obstacles, and when I finish my studies I wish to work in His<br>
service by working for the Church as a librarian. While I have a preference<br>
for working at Andrews University or another midwestern SDA university, I will<br>
keep my mind open to go where the Lord knows my skills will be most needed.<br>
But I need to know where the openings are so that I can do my part in looking<br>
for work. I know with prayer and trust, the Lord will guide me to the right<br>
place. If anyone has information regarding this please send me a message as<br>
soon as you can.<br>
