<title>Jun_1992: Gifts of the Spirit</title>
<h1>Gifts of the Spirit</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 25 Jun 1992 20:30:06 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#30">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#30">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#30">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#30">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Bill Nickless: "SDAnet traffic history"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0029.html">Glen Pringle: "Re: Gifts of the Spirit"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0029.html">Glen Pringle: "Re: Gifts of the Spirit"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some of you are most likely acquainted with the Spiritual Gifts <br>
Inventory, developed by Cruz and Naden at the SDA Theological Seminary.<br>
In seminars which are given in SDA churches, this survey is given to <br>
people and through it people discover what spiritual gifts they have.<br>
This then serves as a guide to know what church offices or projects one<br>
should volunteer to help with, or people can voluntarily submit this <br>
information to the nominating committee to guide them as they are making <br>
decisions about who will serve as officers.  I have observed that this<br>
survey and the associated seminar was quite helpful to our church in<br>
Pittsburgh<br>
in helping us understand where we could be used.<br>
<p>
But a question I posed at that seminar, which was not answered to my<br>
satisfaction at that time and still troubles me to some extent, is this.<br>
If we see that a certain gift is missing from our church, what should we<br>
do about it?  Must we be content with the gifts we have already, or<br>
should we ask for more?  Is it appropriate to ask for a specific<br>
spiritual gift?<br>
<p>
As I read the Bible, it is appropriate:  1 Cor. 14:1  "Follow after<br>
charity, and desire spiritual gifts, but rather that ye may prophesy."<br>
When was the last time any of us prayed for the gift of prophecy?  Or<br>
the gift of tongues, for that matter?  We know that "...your Heavenly<br>
Father shall give the Holy Spirit to them that ask Him."<br>
<p>
Are we asking?  Are we ready to receive?  Or is the Spirit already among<br>
us, working, and most of us don't even know it?<br>
<p>
I hope we can build a doctrinal and practical discussion on the Holy<br>
Spirit here on SDAnet, but more importantly I hope we can know the<br>
working of the Spirit in our lives both individually and corporately.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
