<!-- received="Mon Jan 01 01:01:01 1990 PST" -->
<!-- sent="Thu, 25 Jun 1992 20:58:10 -0400 (EDT)" -->
<!-- name="Steven Timm" -->
<!-- email="st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu" -->
<!-- subject="alt.sdanet" -->
<!-- id="QeGaiWu00WB6QQ5HV9@andrew.cmu.edu" -->
<!-- inreplyto="" -->
<title>Jun_1992: alt.sdanet</title>
<h1>alt.sdanet</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 25 Jun 1992 20:58:10 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#33">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#33">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#33">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#33">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0034.html">McCluskey G: "Re: school choice, church and state"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0032.html">Steven Timm: "School Choice, Church and State"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0038.html">Stan Macasieb: "Re: alt.sdanet"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
When I first had the idea of starting SDAnet two years ago, I thought about <br>
making a Usenet newsgroup, but soon realized that we could never win the <br>
vote that would be required to create a new newsgroup.  This intuition<br>
proved right as over the last year we have seen proposals for<br>
soc.religion.mormon and soc.religion.christian.catholic go down to<br>
defeat.  There seems to be a widespread feeling on the net that a<br>
mainstream newsgroup should not be <br>
devoted to just one denomination.<br>
<p>
With an alt type group though, there is no requirement for a vote.  All<br>
that's required is some discussion in alt.config and then having a<br>
system administrator start the new group.  It appears like my system<br>
admins will be willing to do this if it's something I want to do.<br>
<p>
So, does anyone have any feedback on this idea.  It would be possible to <br>
have this group created with moderation.  Just like the idea of putting<br>
SDA-L out for public view, it's not something that has to be done, just<br>
a possibility that might be interesting to try, I am not sure myself if<br>
I should do it yet.  It might be helpful to know how many have access to<br>
Usenet news, I can tell from the addresses that many readers of SDAnet<br>
do not and we would still have to have a mailing list of some sort<br>
regardless.<br>
<p>
 From September of 1992 onwards, I will finally have the opportunity to<br>
monitor the net with all the glory of X Windows which is the mailing<br>
system at Carnegie Mellon.  I will be in Pittsburgh for the fall<br>
semester to take some classes.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
