<!-- body="start" -->
This chart shows the course of traffic on SDAnet, with one X<br>
representing 10 kilobytes of data.  After the point marked it also includes<br>
traffic from SDA-L, also stored in our archives.<br>
<p>
JUN 90 X<br>
JUL 90 XXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
AUG 90 X<br>
SEP 90 XXX<br>
OCT 90 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
NOV 90 XXXX<br>
DEC 90 XXXXXXXXXX<br>
JAN 91 XXXXX<br>
FEB 91 XXXXXXXXXX<br>
MAR 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
APR 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX  !SDA-L merger<br>
MAY 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
JUN 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
JUL 91 XXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
AUG 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
SEP 91 XXXXXXXX<br>
OCT 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
NOV 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
DEC 91 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
JAN 92 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
FEB 92 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
MAR 92 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
APR 92 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
MAY 92 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br>
<p>
Integrated total is 4.3 Megabytes so far.  At least half of that <br>
is probably the extra headers put on by Carnegie Mellon's mail system.<br>
Peak number of messages in any one month is 200, also in April 91.<br>
We have done 60-message weeks, but never kept up the intensity that hard for<br>
a whole month.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
