<title>Jun_1992: SDAnet is 2 years old today</title>
<h1>SDAnet is 2 years old today</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 25 Jun 1992 09:54:49 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#40">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#40">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#40">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#40">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0041.html">Stan Macasieb: "Re: School Choice, Church and State"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0039.html">Steven Timm: "SDAnet traffic history"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
It seems hard to believe, but we have been on the air for two years now.<br>
 From the small beginning with seven subscribers we have grown to what <br>
we are now.<br>
<p>
I had planned to prepare a feature on the best of SDAnet over the first two<br>
years, but I've been unable to log on to the machine where I keep the<br>
archives for the last couple of days.  Over the past two years we have <br>
generated several megabytes of postings and grown to almost 100 subscribers.<br>
<p>
<p>
Thanks everyone for your support, whether you have been with us from the <br>
beginning or just joined recently.  Remember, members come to SDAnet most <br>
frequently the same way they come to church, by personal invitation and by <br>
word of mouth.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
