Since you do moderate, do think you might consider putting sdanet on a<br>
digest format?  It certainly would remove a lot of clutter of<br>
maintaining tons of individual e-mails.<br>
<p>
Just my 2 cents.<br>
<p>
Thanks.<br>
<p>
Danny<br>
[I have considered this, and even offered to do it from time to time, <br>
but the interest hasn't been there.  It would be a lot more work <br>
for me since my system doesn't lend itself easily to concatenating<br>
messages.  The advantages would be that everyone would get only one or<br>
two messages a day instead of the 5-10 we have been averaging lately.<br>
It would also cut down on extra-=short posts and reduce the relative<br>
volume of headers in the messages.  The disadvantages, besides making <br>
more work for me, is that it would be harder to respond to original <br>
senders via E-mail, harder to keep a discussion thread going, and <br>
people would have to read through all the articles to see the ones they<br>
want to read.  Let me know what you think about this.  SCT]<br>
