<title>Feb_1992: Great Youth Success in Chicago</title>
<h1>Great Youth Success in Chicago</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun,  9 Feb 1992 18:18:29 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#81">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#81">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#81">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#81">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Paul Gates: "Re:  "Inspiration" by Alden Thompson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0080.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Pastors who seem uncommitted"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Over this past weekend, the Chicagoland Youth Association (CHIYA),<br>
of which I am secretary, held our annual youth rally at Hinsdale Jr. Academy.<br>
The local Hinsdale leaders (whom I also help) gave the Friday night program,<br>
which we call "Prime Time."  The goal of Prime Time is to communicate Jesus<br>
through all of the most contemporary methods possible.  We accomplish <br>
this through skits, contemporary music, and well-focused speakers.  We had <br>
130 people at our program, double our previous best.<br>
<p>
For the day on Sabbath we expected in our wildest dreams only 200 to come.<br>
But we were blessed with almost 300 young people there.  Randy Wisbey,<br>
of the Youth Resource Center at Andrews University, lined up the various<br>
groups that helped make the day.  Kelli Wright, a student missionary, <br>
gave a talk and an afternoon seminar on mission opportunities.  The<br>
"Impressions" drama group from Andrews University gave some compelling<br>
drama.  Brett Barry, recording artist with Crossroads Records, ministered<br>
mightily through his music and his sharing Jesus.  At the end of the day <br>
he gave a call and many teens stepped forward, saying they wanted to <br>
follow Jesus.  <br>
<p>
Again I'm overwhelmed at the way God is leading in our area.  The local <br>
youth leaders all sense the tremendous sense of responsibility that now<br>
rests on us, discipling this young people.  Praise God and pray for us.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
