<title>Aug2_1994: Pro-Life, period &lt;Re: Abortion and all that&gt;</title>
<h1>Pro-Life, period &lt;Re: Abortion and all that&gt;</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 14 Aug 94 16:04:23 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#37">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#37">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#37">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#37">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0038.html">Dan Crowe: "Re: How do we offer PRAISE?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0036.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "Our Great Mobile God"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0075.html">Joseph Miceli: "Re: Pro-Life, period &lt;Re: Abortion and all that&gt;"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Joseph I admire your stand on counting unborn fetuses as<br>
living beings.  The point I feel that many of us Pro-Lifers<br>
miss, is that life does not end at birth.  The fetus is not on its<br>
own once born.  The parent(s) isn't/aren't on his/her/their own.<br>
What government agency will track parents to babies who<br>
might be orphaned?  Will the Church do it?  Where is the<br>
money going to come from to provide for _all_ would be<br>
aborted babies?  Where will the earth hold all the people?<br>
How will the cities survive with the expedited population<br>
increasing?  How will we manage the earth?  Who will be<br>
responsible for making sure people aren't living "reckless<br>
and 'valueless lifestyles'?"  (Note:  They _do_ have values,<br>
just not some of the ones you might have.  Or maybe they<br>
have values like you in this area but felt that they had to<br>
make a choice against the nature of those values.  Neither of<br>
us are judge since we aren't those people.)<br>
<p>
Who will provide families for _all_ unwanted babies?<br>
Is physical life without a family that wants you, better than not<br>
having lived in the first place?  Who will support youth who<br>
are disowned by families?<br>
<p>
Are we good stewards of the earth and keepers of each other<br>
in continually having new babies while many others that are<br>
already born are without families, complaining any time tax<br>
is needed to support them?<br>
<p>
The point is, is that we _don't_, we *do NOT*, know anything<br>
on the personal situations of many, nor on concrete alternatives<br>
to keep this planet from plunging into chaos of greater cosmic<br>
proportion, through over-population, or infringement of certain<br>
governmental rights, or privacy.<br>
<p>
(A perfect cartoon I saw recently had a multitude of hungry,<br>
apparently malnourished people, holding empty bowls, from<br>
foreground to infinity.  In the sky were the words,<br>
"Global Over-population," Also in the foreground was a notable<br>
"clergy" who had blinders on (like those put on work animals)<br>
but these were in the appearance of a Bible.  On the inside of one<br>
of the "blinders" were the words "Be Fruitful and Multiply."<br>
He stood smiling with hands cupped in "praying position" while<br>
pained faces were all around.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
