I finaly got to see what internet is all about.  The UT library has a public<br>
internet terminal.  So out of curiosity, I logged in as per directions, and<br>
called up a list of gophers, after wading through a couple of menus, I found<br>
the Andrews gopher.  It was eye opening.  I decided to access JeWeL, and look<br>
up a book that I had the library aquire back in 1975 or so for me.  Sure<br>
enough, it is still there.  "The Making of a Genius" by Aron Stern.  A<br>
facinating book.  This man essentially programmed his daughter.  She had<br>
her PHD by the time she was 16 I think.  It details the steps that he went<br>
through, and his thesis through out the book, is that with proper training<br>
you can make any kid into a genius.  Now, The real question, and one<br>
for Harvey, is "How many times has this book been checked out".  The<br>
first checkout is of course, me, but it would be interesting to know of<br>
any others.  I would hope it got some use.  JeWeL is nice.  <br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
