<!-- body="start" -->
the spirit is the "breath of life". That is amply born out throughout<br>
the bible, and is in fact, a main tenent of our stance on the state of<br>
the dead.  Therefore the fetus becomes a person at birth...<br>
I personally, feel that the current guidlines are fine.  They hold that<br>
if the fetus would have a chance of surviving if born at that time, then<br>
abortion is not permitted except to save the life of the mother, or in<br>
severe congenital deformities (Generaly this is at the start of the<br>
third tri-mester, or at 6 months of gestation).<br>
Before that, it would be a non-survivable situation.  This makes perfect<br>
sense to a zoologist like me.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
