<title>Aug2_1994: Babies Update</title>
<h1>Babies Update</h1>
Carlyle B. Edwards (<i>carlyle@iquest.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Aug 1994 23:50:45 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#6">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#6">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#6">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#6">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0007.html">DAVESPARKS@delphi.com: "Re: What does it mean?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Harry Salvini: "Re: The motorized throne of God [found it!]"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0052.html">Joseph Miceli: "Re: Babies Update"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Well, the blessed event finally happened!   Our twins (a girl and a boy)<br>
were born and they will have their own identity in having their own birthday<br>
as well.<br>
<p>
              Sarah Katharine Edwards was born on August 11th at 11:54 pm.<br>
 		She weighed in at 7 lbs. 5 oz. and was 20.5 inches in length.<br>
	  	She was in perfect health, except for being born with a<br>
 		cleft lip and cleft palate which can easily be repaired.<br>
                In spite of the cleft lip and palate, she is able to nurse<br>
                with a little assistance.      <br>
<p>
	       Brian Matthew Edwards was born on August 12th at 12:08 am.<br>
 		He weighed in at 6 lbs. 13 oz. and was 19.5 inches in length.<br>
		He was in perfect health, although he had a minor problem with<br>
		rapid breathing at first (which is not unusual for early<br>
                births, 4 weeks before term, and especially with the smaller <br>
                of twins).  He was in ICU for a few hours and has been moved<br>
                to the progressive care nursery and should be back in the<br>
                well baby nursery by sometime Sabbath afternoon. <br>
                  <br>
<p>
We were a little surprised and Sandra's (my wife) first reaction after Sarah<br>
was born was turning to me and saying I'm sorry.  Both the doctor and I told<br>
her that it was not her fault or anyone's fault (except possibly the<br>
old devil's) and that it will be easily repairable to the point where no one<br>
should even notice later on; for I am living proof of what can be done, and<br>
medicine/surgery has progressed quite abit in the past 37 years.<br>
<p>
I/We appreciate everyone's prayers up to this point and I request that you<br>
continue praying for the following requests:<br>
<p>
               1.  That the Lord will guide and direct the surgeon's hands,<br>
                   mind, etc. as he performs the first of several surgeries<br>
                   sometime next week on Sarah.<br>
               2.  That the Lord will continue to draw close to my wife and<br>
                   reassure her that He is able to turn this minor twist<br>
                   into a positive outcome! and that Sarah is truly our<br>
                   "pure princess" (which is essentially what her name<br>
                   means). <br>
<p>
               3.  That He will guide and direct us in our finances and<br>
                   to where He wants us to be as far as employment for<br>
                   me.<br>
<p>
The Lord is good and as He has promised in Psalms 89:33,34 (RSV)<br>
"but I will not remove from him my steadfast love, or be false to<br>
my faithfulness.  I will not violate my covenant OR alter the word <br>
that went forth from my lips."<br>
<p>
Hope everyone had a joyous beginning to their Sabbath and has a blessed<br>
Sabbath day.<br>
<p>
Carlyle B. Edwards<br>
carlyle@iquest.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
