Congrats, Tony, you now know one.  I am pro-choice and don't mind<br>
saying so.  I believe that all knowlege is a learned thing, and that a<br>
pre-born has no way of aquireing any knowlege, therefore is not a<br>
human being in the normal sense of the word.  It is, a physiological<br>
human body, but not an individual yet.  That does not start happening<br>
until at birth.<br>
If a feotus is non-viable, then I have absolutly no problem with aborting<br>
it.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
