<p>
   Hello,<br>
<p>
   How are you?  I saw your message prior to Sabbath Friday and became <br>
excited that 'Europe' has the insight in using a BBS system with the <br>
Internet.  I'm an expert in the setting-up and maintenance of TBBS BBS <br>
systems.  TBBS is the world's leader in corporate BBS systems and is <br>
multi-lingual, also.<br>
<p>
   I've done a large amount of consulting and have setup BBSes for Canon, <br>
CSULB, CPI, and governmental agencies.  I'm also very well versed in the <br>
Internet.  *PLUS*, TBBS is releasing a new, yet already beta tested, <br>
IPAD--The Internet Protocol Adapter.  The *only* PC software/hardware <br>
program that can do all Internet features on a PC.  For example, TELNET, <br>
FTPing, PING, FINGER, and full domain server functions.  <br>
<p>
  I'm not sure if you're looking for someone to just help you, sell to <br>
you, come over there and setup, or what exactly.  Please give me a <br>
snailmail address (regular address) and I will mail you complete <br>
information plus some other good things.  <br>
<p>
  Feel free to e-mail me here or at bishop@csulb.edu anytime!<br>
<p>
  Thank you and God richly bless you in this project!<br>
