To Jesse Lambeth (and others interested)<br>
<p>
Check with your Union Conference (not the state conf) Education<br>
Secretary or whatever the title might be. In the Lake Union the<br>
Education Dept. does an annual audit of the educational situation<br>
at the various academies. Nearly every aspect of educational<br>
situation is covered including standardized testing results,<br>
and various other comparisons. It is available to any SDA parent<br>
interested in the info. You may have to simply go to the Union Conf<br>
office and sit down with the big binder and read it there, but it<br>
is worth it.<br>
<p>
Grades from individual schools should be available--like the<br>
Nelson Denny reading test, and others like the California Aptitude<br>
or SAT.<br>
<p>
Just poke around and ask the educators near where you live.<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
sands@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
