<title>Aug2_1994: Our Great Mobile God</title>
<h1>Our Great Mobile God</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sun, 14 Aug 1994 18:41:57 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#36">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#36">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#36">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#36">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0037.html">Marcus Stringer: "Pro-Life, period &lt;Re: Abortion and all that&gt;"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0035.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "Dr. Hasel's Funeral"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Joseph,<br>
<p>
Why try to make everything revealed about God into a symbol<br>
which might mean something else. The writer of Ezekiel and<br>
Hebrews and Daniel seem to have a good grasp of their God and<br>
God's spiritual aspects.<br>
<p>
They used their eyes and then their brains and then their tongues<br>
and pens to share what they have been shown.<br>
<p>
If they saw "wheel-like" things that is what they saw. Something<br>
capable of transporting through space and it had wheels.<br>
<p>
As far as the question: When did Jesus enter the Most Holy Place,<br>
there is no question that he entered when he ascended. What we don<br>
do not know is how many times Jesus has entered the MHP in his<br>
ministrations. The earthly High Priest entered the MHP at least<br>
five times on the day of atonement.<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
sands@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
