<title>Aug2_1994: Abortion response</title>
<h1>Abortion response</h1>
<i>KevJames@aol.com</i><br>
<i>Sun, 14 Aug 94 23:00:06 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#45">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#45">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#45">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#45">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0046.html">Dennis Murphy: ""absent from the body... home with the Lord""</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0044.html">SDA Net: "Re: Close of probation (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I am addressing Tony Dyson's and George Tasker's comments.  First, Tony's.<br>
<p>
He mentioned that all abortion is sin and gives examples of other sins like<br>
pain, death, etc.  One thing to point out.  These are really not sins as much<br>
as they are results of sin.  I don't think I sinning when I am hurting.  A<br>
minor point, perhaps, but one that needs clarification.<br>
<p>
George Tasker mentioned something about the viability of abortion in<br>
preventing possible propagation of "rapists."  Well, in that line of thinking<br>
I am afraid we should all be aborted.  We all carry fouled genetic material.<br>
 The power of sin is transmitted to us from one generation to the next and<br>
makes us all prone to do terrible things.  I am not stating my views on<br>
abortion's rightness or wrongness, just challenging the logic behind why<br>
certain abortions are "good."<br>
<p>
Point three, would be I think that the issue of abortion is really not to be<br>
the focus.  What I mean is prevention needs to be given more emphasis.  We<br>
need a stronger, clearer, consistant message about total abstinance than is<br>
given by the Christian culture.  An emphasis upon the awesome responsibility<br>
we should have over the gift of pro-creation that God has given each one.  It<br>
is not a toy to be played with.<br>
<p>
Sex was not primarily intended for pleasure, as I understand the Scripture.<br>
 It is primarily for "being fruitful and multiplying."  Pleasure and bonding<br>
are by-products if you will.  Such biblical concepts accepted and respected<br>
with go along ways in preventing abortion.  Any comments on this?<br>
<p>
Kevin James<br>
KevJames@aol.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
