<!-- body="start" -->
How do others of you understand the scriptures in 2 Cor 5:6-9 and Phil 1:23-24<br>
in which the apostle Paul mentions his preference to be "absent from the body"<br>
or to "depart", and thus in both cases to be with the Lord?  I don't believe<br>
the Scripture contradicts itself, therefore I wonder how those words harmonize<br>
with many other scriptures which describe a person's condition in death as<br>
similar to sleep.  To date, I have simply waited for a fuller understanding of<br>
those verses, but recently someone has asked about them and before I respond I<br>
would to hear of any other ideas.<br>
<p>
Reply either directly to me or back onto the SDAnet.<br>
<p>
Thanks for your help.<br>
--Dennis, sleeping at my terminal (zzzzzzzzz)<br>
  E-mail: un041345@wvnvms.wvnet.edu<br>
