<title>Aug2_1994: when does life begin?</title>
<h1>when does life begin?</h1>
Benjamin Siyowi Mapani (<i>lole@ariel.ucs.unimelb.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 12:18:04 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#42">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#42">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#42">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#42">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0043.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Close of probation"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0041.html">DAVESPARKS@delphi.com: "Re: How do we offer PRAISE?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
When the sperm unites with the ovum, does life begin then?<br>
If not, is the fetus dead at that stage, such that its not<br>
alive? If so then when does it begin to live? at how many<br>
minutes, hours, days, weeks, or is it uniquely after its<br>
born?<br>
Ben<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
