<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Abortion and all that</title>
<h1>Re: Abortion and all that</h1>
GEORGE TASKER (<i>taskerg@jasper.cqu.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 13:26:19 +1000 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#47">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#47">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#47">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#47">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0048.html">Carlyle B. Edwards: "Re: Is abortion sin? (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0046.html">Dennis Murphy: ""absent from the body... home with the Lord""</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In-Reply-&gt;To: &lt;38@reason.win.net&gt; from "Joseph Miceli" at Aug 13, 94 11:52:09 am<br>
<p>
I consider myself very fortunate that out of the life threatening <br>
circumsances that we experience that I have two lovely boys that I am so <br>
proud of.  My referral to abortion etc. was the result of my mind wandering <br>
off into the weirdest of places which it is prone to do when reading as I am <br>
typing.<br>
<p>
A memory has been jogged as the result of reading other people's thoughts on <br>
the topic.  I remember coming across a girl who told me how she fell <br>
pregnant to a boyfriend and her thinking was that she would be punishing the <br>
child which she had simply on account of their actions and to her it did not <br>
seem fair that this unborn should be punished for what they had chosen to <br>
do.<br>
<p>
I think that there is a lot of merit in that thought.  It seems that as a <br>
general society is punishing the innocent unborn, sentencing them to death <br>
for things of which they themselves are guilty.  Is this what we mean by <br>
human sacrifice?<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
George Tasker                                 taskerg@topaz.cqu.edu.au
                                              taskerg@jasper.cqu.edu.au
<p>
Blessed is the man that hath nothing to say and cannot be persuaded to say it.
Hezekiah 5:9
</pre>
