<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Is abortion sin?</title>
<h1>Re: Is abortion sin?</h1>
Raylene Dyson (<i>CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 15:45:33 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#49">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#49">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#49">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#49">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0050.html">Joseph Miceli: "Re: Is abortion sin? (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0048.html">Carlyle B. Edwards: "Re: Is abortion sin? (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;story, that abortion will provide a solution to the problem, women</i><br>
<i>&gt;often consent to pressure from the man, only to find that they</i><br>
<i>&gt;suffer from post-abortion syndrom, which manifests itself in a</i><br>
<i>&gt;variety of ways.  Depression and anger are common, and a deep</i><br>
<i>&gt;seated sense of guilt sometimes torments the woman for years,</i><br>
<i>&gt;especially when she later carries a wanted baby to term.  </i><br>
<p>
I wouldn't like to see forgotten the men who refused women abortions<br>
when perhaps they should have been done.<br>
Wasn't there an Irish case (exceptional of course) not too long ago where<br>
a rape victim was not allowed an abortion in Ireland and (for a while)<br>
was not allowed to leave the country to get one.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;protected, then do so.  But need we continue the abortion on</i><br>
<i>&gt;demand industry so that men and women can pursue a reckless and</i><br>
<i>&gt;valueless lifestyle at the expense of innocent children?</i><br>
<p>
I feel the industry must be maintained.<br>
<p>
Its all the big sin problem. I'd rather see children not be given the<br>
chance to live than to grow up unwanted. So many of our societal problems<br>
stem from children being abused or ignored by their parents.<br>
<p>
When the children that are born are all loved, then I'll start picketing the<br>
abortion clinics.<br>
<p>
On the other hand, I do rather value my own life!<br>
Raylene<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
