<title>Aug2_1994: What is NLP</title>
<h1>What is NLP</h1>
Ralf Simonsson (<i>/G=Ralf/S=Simonsson/O=Fimnet/@elisa.fi</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 18:43:49 +0300</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#58">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#58">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#58">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#58">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0059.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: #2 response to Internet Replies/ASDAL"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0057.html">SDA Net: "What is NLP (fwd)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Kansion nimi:          Postikansio<br>
Viestin absoluuttinro: 41072<br>
Viestin rel.nro:       82<br>
Koko:                  2497<br>
Dokumentin nimi:       What is NLP<br>
=============================TEKSTIN ALKU==========================<br>
Neurolinquistic programming (NLP) is said to be a new language in <br>
psychology, but is difficult to give an exact definition for it. It has not <br>
grown from some guru or around a theory. It is more like a plant that has <br>
roots in diverse areas and sciences and on it is continuously growing new <br>
leaves.<br>
<p>
Anyhow there are some basic presumptions which clarify the ideas behind <br>
NLP. Eg. the terrain is the same for everybody, but one is making his own <br>
map of it, depending on his genes and on experiences. When we understand <br>
this, we can also understand why people are not always ready to accept our <br>
truth. They have a different map of the terrain.<br>
<p>
NLP is helping us in communication with each other. We can see that their <br>
concept is a visual one (they see things clearly), or if it sounds OK <br>
(auditive) or if they have a burden about something (kinestetic). We will <br>
see their feelings in their fysiology (body language). <br>
<p>
In everyday life we are using the language patterns of NLP, knowingly or <br>
unknowingly. We might say to a person: "If you get well, then you can..." <br>
or "when you get well, then you can.." By choosing our wording we can <br>
create a positive or doubting effect. Of course, you might think this is to <br>
control the mind!<br>
<p>
In therapy one has created neurolinquistic programming by modelling  top <br>
specialists or therapeutists - looking closely how they are "functioning", <br>
how they are talking. By using their techniques (linquistic programs) we <br>
get access to their skills.<br>
<p>
You can use NLP in planning your future or when confronting frightening <br>
things from the past. Of course you could use just prayer to meet the <br>
future or the past. But maybe our prayers would be more effective, when we <br>
know ourselves better. NLP is a good *tool* to find out about us and <br>
others.<br>
<p>
There are many other leaves in the tree of NLP, it has been written lots of <br>
books anout it during the last 20 years. I like to see NLP as fishing, you <br>
need not eat all the fish you get, you just choose the best ones. NLP a <br>
devils tool? - sure - the devil is using the Bible very cleverly, too, when <br>
it suits his plans.<br>
<p>
BTW it would be interesting to know if somebody has used NLP in for <br>
instance stop-smoking seminars and weight control programs.<br>
<p>
Airi Simonsson<br>
Ralf Simonsson<br>
Internet: Ralf.Simonsson/O=Fimnet/@elisa.fi         RSi@fimnet.fi           <br>
 <br>
          rasimons@freenet.hut.fi<br>
X.400:    S=Simonsson/G=Ralf/O=Fimnet/ADMD=Elisa/C=FI<br>
Tel +358 (9)49100230     fax: + 358 (9)0-3930773<br>
<p>
Ralf Simonsson<br>
X400: S=Simonsson, G=Ralf, O=Fimnet,  A=elisa, C=Fi<br>
Internet: Ralf.Simonsson/O=fimnet/@elisa.fi or rsi@fimnet.fi<br>
