<title>Aug2_1994: Poor Wording of Intro to APA Statement...</title>
<h1>Poor Wording of Intro to APA Statement...</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 19:07:43 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#69">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#69">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#69">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#69">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0070.html">Joseph Miceli: "Re: Punishment vs consequences"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0068.html">SDA Net: "SDA Abortion Statement"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 From Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
<p>
The wording which I used to introduce the APA statement about<br>
Lesbians/Gays/Bisexuals was unfortunate. I meant to convey<br>
that I was encouraged by this resolution because these groups,<br>
who are discriminated against, are correct in their self-defense.<br>
<p>
I apologize for the original wording of my intro.<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
