<title>Aug2_1994: WARNNING OR CHURCH UNITY</title>
<h1>WARNNING OR CHURCH UNITY</h1>
Barrington Brennen (<i>brennen@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 15 Aug 1994 19:37:01 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#71">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#71">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#71">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#71">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0072.html">Tony Dyson: "Another hypothetical"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0070.html">Joseph Miceli: "Re: Punishment vs consequences"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Sunday August 14, 1994 I posted a response to GC president remarks on<br>
Church unity and diversity he made at the recent televised ASI<br>
convention.  <br>
<p>
I want to continue with a WARNING ABOUT UNITY.  <br>
<p>
The problem is that when the subject comes us about blakc and white<br>
churches the idea is that the black conferences or church will disband.<br>
If this is the concept that we will be going backwards. I believe that<br>
all unions and conferences would need to be re-organized.  Away will<br>
this seperation.   <br>
<p>
I am not supporting "membership bussing."  I am support open<br>
administration to all colors and ethnic groups.  Stop placing people<br>
with boxes.   <br>
<p>
Do you know that some "black leaders" and saying that the NAACP is no<br>
longer relevant.  I also believe that Regional Conference are not longer<br>
relevant.  The are doing more harm than good.   A real reason why many<br>
refuse to touch this problem even with a ten foot pole is because is a<br>
all about POWER and position.<br>
<p>
I challendge the first Black or White pastor who would take the bull by<br>
the horn.  Do for it.<br>
<p>
That is GO FOR IT!!..<br>
<p>
I FIRMLY BELIEVE THAT IF SOMETHING DOES NOT HAPPEN SOON TO CHANGE THE<br>
FACE OF OUR CHURCH, WE WILL PUBLICALLY EMBARRASED AGAIN.  And this time<br>
more terriably.<br>
<p>
Let's get going.  IF WE CAN'T LIVE AND WORSHIP TOGETHER ON EARTH, we<br>
will not be able to do it in heaven, in fact we will not get there.<br>
<p>
<p>
Barrington Brennen<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
