<title>Aug2_1994: Abortion &amp; Contraception</title>
<h1>Abortion &amp; Contraception</h1>
Ted Barker (<i>tbarker@sun004.cpdsc.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 16 Aug 94 08:31:28 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#78">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#78">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#78">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#78">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0079.html">AMY HACK: "Re[2]: Pastors"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0077.html">Stanleyned G. Macasieb: "Good-bye, for now"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0097.html">DAVESPARKS@delphi.com: "Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
What would the Operation Rescue activists do if someone were to attend one<br>
of their protests and start saying "PREVENT abortions!" quietly and hand<br>
out condoms and spermacide to everyone in sight?<br>
<p>
There is often far too little wisdom in debates on abortion, so it is truly<br>
miraculous that the corporate church was able to develop such a wise policy<br>
on abortion.<br>
<p>
Abortion is a terrible means of birth control. Aging self-righteous _men_<br>
and bureaucrats have no business dictating to the individual woman what she<br>
is going to do with her body. As a man, I would not mind at all if men were<br>
not even allowed to discuss abortion, let alone make laws regarding it.<br>
<p>
_______________________________________________________________<br>
Theo "Ted" Barker                             tbarker@cpdsc.com<br>
SW Engr.                                           214-519-7927<br>
DSC Communications Corp., Broadband Products Div., Dallas<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
