In-Reply-&gt;To: &lt;Pine.3.05.9408141648.A24242-9100000@ecf.puc.edu&gt; from "Dan Crowe" at Aug 14, 94 04:41:20 pm<br>
<p>
It was once suggested to me that:-<br>
    thanksgiving - involves what God has done<br>
    praise       - involves who God is (His character, e.g., Exo 34:6,7)<br>
<p>
I found the distinction interesting; unfortunately, I haven't yet come across<br>
support for making this distinction.  Can anyone help on this?<br>
