<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Breath or Blood</title>
<h1>Re: Breath or Blood</h1>
Woody Baker (<i>woody@knapper.cactus.org</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 16 Aug 1994 10:09:41 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#80">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#80">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#80">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#80">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0081.html">Woody Baker: "Re: #2 response to Internet Replies/ASDAL"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0079.html">AMY HACK: "Re[2]: Pastors"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0033.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "Breath or Blood"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0112.html">Dan Blake: "Re: Breath or Blood"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Bill, the blood carries oxegen.  Believe it or not, there are now<br>
synthetic blood subsitutes.  They don't carry the defenses that blood does,<br>
but they will transport oxegen, and can be used to replace blood for<br>
that purpose.  Life is in the Blood, only in the sense that the blood<br>
provides nutrients, and gasses to the cells, and removes waste products.<br>
You can have all the blood circulating in your body that you need, but<br>
if you aren't oxegenation it, and removing CO2, i.e. breathing, you<br>
are going to be dead very shortly.  The cells will starve for oxegen.<br>
I think the way the bible puts it, is once again a cultural artifact<br>
in this sense:  Back then science was an empirical thing.  You let the<br>
blood out of an animal, and it dies.  Therefore the life is in the blood.<br>
I think that the Lord had to put it that way, so the people could<br>
understand.  Consider what this would mean to the bible folk,<br>
"You shall not eat the blood of the animal, because the blood supplies<br>
oxegen to the cells, the blood removes waste products, and is processed<br>
by the liver."<br>
None of these things were known at that time.<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker 		woody@knapper.cactus.org
Contract programmer/Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  
Aurora Contracting 512-272-4511 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
</pre>
