decide to retire or remove the book, I would like to have it.<br>
<p>
I think what Aaron Stern did was wonderful.  The ultimate programming<br>
enviornment.  Actually he did very little manipulating, mostly he made<br>
sure that his daughter had a very enriched enviornment.  She was reading<br>
street signs at 3.  He was actually rather shocked when she did that.<br>
<p>
He played classical music at low volume in her nursery, essentially 24<br>
hours a day.  When she was just a few months old, she had already selected<br>
favorite pieces, and would smile when they came on, but frown and cry<br>
when one she did not like was played.  There are many more interesting<br>
tidbits in this book.<br>
