<!-- body="start" -->
        Reply to:   RE&gt;Skunks in EDEN?<br>
<p>
Bill Sands wrote:<br>
<i>&gt;With some of the theological beliefs about life in Eden changing</i><br>
<i>&gt;after the "fall", I wonder if God created skunks in Eden. And</i><br>
<i>&gt;if there were skunks in Eden, why were they equipped with such</i><br>
<i>&gt;a stink...</i><br>
<p>
Just wondering...were there skunks in Eden?<br>
<p>
The following is my own theory; it has no Biblical basis<br>
or reasoning:  Is it possible that skunks were equipped with<br>
the ability to spray that awful scent AFTER the fall,<br>
because the skunk would need some way to repel<br>
larger carnivores that might be inclined to eat them?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;P.S. Will there be skunks in heaven?</i><br>
<p>
I'm wondering if there will be animals in the new heaven,<br>
or will they only be inhabiting the new earth?  Whether<br>
skunks will be present in the new heaven or new earth,<br>
they certainly won't have any reason to be frightened,<br>
so I would think that they wouldn't have any reason to<br>
spray.  Or maybe, since God will make all things new,<br>
the skunk will have a new scent.  ;-)<br>
<p>
Cori Bradford<br>
cbradfor@ida.org<br>
Alexandria, Virginia<br>
