<title>Aug2_1994: Another hypothetical</title>
<h1>Another hypothetical</h1>
Tony Dyson (<i>PHAJD@wombat.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 16 Aug 1994 14:32:06 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#72">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#72">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#72">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#72">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0073.html">Dennis Murphy: "re: abortion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0071.html">Barrington Brennen: "WARNNING OR CHURCH UNITY"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0093.html">Cori Bradford: "Re: Another hypothetical"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
While we're on with the "hypotheticals" here's another one for<br>
you all to ponder.<br>
<p>
Adventist girl and adventist boy in long-standing relationship<br>
have a nasty breakup. Later, girl meets another boy, they become<br>
friends, they date, and then become engaged. A few months before<br>
the wedding date, girl is visited by ex-boyfriend at night. <br>
After a confrontation she is raped by ex-boyfriend, and <br>
consequently falls pregnant. There is no question over the<br>
identity of the father, as this has been the only opportunity<br>
for conception. Ex-boyfriend, upon finding out that girl is<br>
pregnant, makes it clear that he will expect to have a part<br>
in the upbringing of the child.<br>
<p>
It's ridiculous using such hypotheticals as this in these <br>
discussions, isn't it. All I can say is, if hypothetically<br>
you happen to find yourself praying one of these days, perhaps<br>
you could spare a thought for this hypothetical girl and her<br>
fiance - pray that they can now live with whatever hypothetical<br>
decision they may have made in this case.<br>
<p>
	Tony<br>
<p>
ps... Yes I agree that "policy" shouldn't be based on individual<br>
instances. But let's not forget that life is just a whole lot<br>
of individual instances!<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
