Thanx to everyone for your prayers for Reds Eberhardt.<br>
He was released from the hospital yesterday morning.<br>
The doctor told him he could resume his normal activities,<br>
but Reds didn't tell him everything about his activities.<br>
I saw his truck parked in the church parking lot as I<br>
was on my way to work this morning.<br>
Reds called me today and said he was going to<br>
rake the gravel in the church driveway and parking lot.<br>
I'm sure he'll be mowing the lawn tomorrow.<br>
<p>
Reds thanks you for your prayers, too.<br>
<p>
God is good!<br>
<p>
Peace,<br>
<p>
Cori Bradford<br>
cbradfor@ida.org<br>
Alexandria, Virginia<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
