Bill Sands wrote:<br>
<i>&gt;Check with your Union Conference (not the state conf) Education</i><br>
<i>&gt;Secretary or whatever the title might be. In the Lake Union the</i><br>
<i>&gt;Education Dept. does an annual audit of the educational situation</i><br>
<i>&gt;at the various academies. Nearly every aspect of educational</i><br>
<i>&gt;situation is covered including standardized testing results,</i><br>
<i>&gt;and various other comparisons. It is available to any SDA parent</i><br>
<i>&gt;interested in the info. You may have to simply go to the Union Conf</i><br>
<i>&gt;office and sit down with the big binder and read it there, but it</i><br>
<i>&gt;is worth it.</i><br>
<p>
Thanks, Bill. I will try to get that information and compile an "independent"<br>
report if the data will support production of a meaningful report. Of course,<br>
at work, I would produce a report anyway... It would just mean that<br>
more prettier colors would be used. :)<br>
<p>
jesse<br>
