        Reply to:   RE&gt;Are you ready...?<br>
<p>
Steve wrote:<br>
<p>
This past Sabbath we were treated to a special music of that old standby<br>
of many evangelistic meetings, "Are You Ready For Jesus To Come."<br>
<p>
I present the chorus, and then a way I thought of to revise it slightly<br>
to provide a bit more hope.<br>
<p>
The original...<br>
<p>
Are you ready for Jesus to come?<br>
Are you faithful in all that you do?<br>
Have you fought a good fight?<br>
Have you stood for the right?<br>
Can others see Jesus in you?<br>
Are you ready to stand in your place?<br>
Are you ready to look on His face?<br>
Can you look up and say, "This is my Lord."<br>
Are you ready for Jesus to come?<br>
<p>
<p>
New and improved....<br>
Jesus is ready for you to come<br>
He is faithful in all that you do<br>
He has fought the good fight<br>
He has stood for the right,<br>
Helps others see Jesus in you.<br>
He already has stood in your place<br>
He wants you to look on His face<br>
You can look up and say "This is my lord"<br>
Jesus is ready for you to come...<br>
------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Steve, I like this!  I'm going to share it with our music director,<br>
Candie Jefferson.  I know she'll love it.<br>
<p>
Pleasant evening,<br>
<p>
Cori Bradford<br>
cbradfor@ida.org<br>
