Thanks!  You are right, the Lord has truly blessed us.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; My wife and I are expecting our first child in January,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and when I read of new births like those you wrote of, it</i><br>
<i>&gt; thrills me to my soul.  </i><br>
<p>
Great!  We will add the three of you to our prayer list as well!<br>
 <br>
<i>&gt; Your wife has nothing to be sorry for,</i><br>
<i>&gt; and everything to be happy about.  She's just brought into the</i><br>
<i>&gt; world 2 new lives, two babies who will soon be children and then</i><br>
<i>&gt; adults.  </i><br>
<p>
You are absolutely right and she has made a fantastic turnaround after<br>
"being sorry".   I think that all it took was her getting some much<br>
needed sleep, and us praying together, and my hugging her and the babies, etc.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; My wife and I pray our baby will be healthy, but if for</i><br>
<i>&gt; some reason something has gone wrong, we'll lean on the Lord for</i><br>
<i>&gt; strength, knowing that whatever comes, that baby is a blessing</i><br>
<i>&gt; regardless. </i><br>
<p>
And as God has promised, "I will not remove from him my steadfast love,<br>
or be false to my faithfulness.  I will not violate my covenant, or alter<br>
the word that went forth from my lips."  Psalms 89:33,34  I refer to this<br>
as my all encompassing promise.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; The surgery will go fine; tell your wife what a marvelous thing she and </i><br>
<i>&gt; you and the Lord have done, and take pleasure in your beautiful babies.  </i><br>
<i>&gt; God bless you both.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
The first surgery was completed this past monday,  and all did go well!!!<br>
<p>
Sarah went through the surgery and the recovery with flying colors and will<br>
be coming home tomorrow, (wednesday) to rejoin her brother as a vital part<br>
of our family in our home.<br>
<p>
Thanks for everyone's prayers!!!<br>
<p>
Carlyle B. Edwards<br>
