<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Is abortion sin?</title>
<h1>Re: Is abortion sin?</h1>
Woody Baker (<i>woody@knapper.cactus.org</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Aug 1994 08:38:13 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#100">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#100">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#100">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#100">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0101.html">Dan Drazen: "Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0099.html">Craig Kinzer: "Re: 1844  (*^&amp;$%^$&amp;$^)"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I happen to think that Roe vs Wade is not bad law.  It simply establishes<br>
certain guidelines that should be followed, if an abortion is chosen,<br>
and protects the right of the mother to chose such.  In doing such, it<br>
upholds one of the fundamental rights of a human being, that of controlling<br>
ones body.  Additionally, it upholds the bill of rights.<br>
<p>
As to long waiting lists for adoption, that is only because most adoptive<br>
parents are not willing to accept older black children, or handicapped.<br>
Sexually abused children are not generally wanted for adoption.  My wife<br>
has been looking over my shoulder as I write this, and making me correct<br>
things that I had written (grin).  She has been extensively researching<br>
the topic, because we may adopt a kid.  <br>
<p>
To me, it is moraly wrong to bring a child into the world in the state<br>
that it is in.  It is wrong for me to burden the world with one more<br>
mouth to feed.  I sincerely do not believe that I could cope with the<br>
guilt.  Of course that is but one reason that the decision has been<br>
made.  There are many others.<br>
<p>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
<pre>
-- 
Woody Baker 		woody@knapper.cactus.org
Contract programmer/Postscript consultant/Flint knapper  
Aurora Contracting 512-272-4511 (Austin, Tx)
<p>
"If you ain't bleedin' you ain't knappin'" ---&gt; go ahead, ask me...
</pre>
