<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception</title>
<h1>Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception</h1>
Dan Drazen (<i>drazen@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Aug 1994 18:20:26 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#101">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#101">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#101">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#101">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0102.html">Dan Crowe: "Re: "absent from the body... home with the Lord""</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0100.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0078.html">Ted Barker: "Abortion &amp; Contraception"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0108.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In-Reply-&gt;To: &lt;01HG09QZRMWK987WDY@delphi.com&gt; from "DAVESPARKS@delphi.com" at Aug 17, 94 07:07:34 am<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Theo "Ted" Barker wrote:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; What would the Operation Rescue activists do if someone were to attend one</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; of their protests and start saying "PREVENT abortions!" quietly and hand</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; out condoms and spermacide to everyone in sight?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; That would be like holding seminars on "safe bank robbery", methinks!  The</i><br>
<i>&gt; point is, no sin is "safe", perhaps because God designed things that way.</i><br>
<i>&gt; While what you're hypothesizing would be slightly preferable to abortion, I</i><br>
<i>&gt; suppose, it's not the BEST solution.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I don't know what "Operation Rescue" would do.  What do you suppose YOUR</i><br>
<i>&gt; pastor would do if someone tried that in the middle of one of the services</i><br>
<i>&gt; at YOUR church?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;  /--------------+------------------------------------\</i><br>
<i>&gt;  |              |  Internet: davesparks@delphi.com   |</i><br>
<i>&gt;  | Dave Sparks  |  Fidonet:  Dave Sparks @ 1:207/212 |</i><br>
<i>&gt;  |              |  BBS:      (909) 353-9821 - 14.4K  |</i><br>
<i>&gt;  \--------------+------------------------------------/</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
"Safe bank robbery"?  Gimme a break!<br>
<p>
There are two issues involved here.  There's your statement that "no sin<br>
is safe" used in the context of describing contraception.  Whether<br>
contraception is a sin depends on whom you talk to.  Certainly the Roman<br>
Catholic wing of the anti-abortion movement is also going to be<br>
anti-contraception [if they're following the party line laid down in the<br>
encyclical _Humanae Vitae_].  Their thinking is that the entire<br>
procreative process is God-directed and shouldn't involve human<br>
tampering.<br>
<p>
Second is the question of conscience.  The biggest problem I've had with<br>
the abortion question has nothing to do with such esoterica as when life<br>
begins.  It all comes down to: whose life is it, yours or Pat<br>
Robertson's?  Who made him [and others in the anti-abortion movement]<br>
the arbiters of moral choice in this society?  Whether one agrees with<br>
them in any particular question is another issue.  When someone sets it<br>
up so you have no choice in moral questions, are you really being all<br>
that religious on your own?<br>
<p>
I've got no answers -- just a bunch more interesting questions.  Some of<br>
them involve my cat.<br>
<p>
Daniel J. Drazen<br>
Editor, SDA Periodical Index<br>
