<title>Aug2_1994: A Peculiar People?</title>
<h1>A Peculiar People?</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 17 Aug 1994 20:45:53 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#109">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#109">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#109">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#109">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0110.html">GEORGE TASKER: "More thoughts on abortion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0108.html">Woody Baker: "Re: Abortion &amp; Contraception"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0129.html">DAVESPARKS@delphi.com: "Re: A Peculiar People?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
IF Ellen White is merely an anachronism of the 19th century,<br>
and IF the 2300 days did not end in 1844,<br>
what reason is there for a denomination called the<br>
Seventh-day Adventist Church?<br>
<p>
IF there is no special significance to the heavenly sanctuary<br>
with regard to Daniel 8:14, why do we bother to perpetuate<br>
our church?<br>
<p>
If there are no special or unique messages or beliefs<br>
why should we continue? Why not disband and drop it all<br>
as a GREAT DISAPPOINTMENT?<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
