Hello !<br>
       In last time I have read many posts about Christ in the Sanctuary.<br>
One of them shows Heb 6:19 as a "proof" to say that Jesus go into the <br>
Most Holy Place just after his asention (sp ?) to Heaven. This fact gave<br>
opotunity for a discusion about the mobility of God's trone.<br>
<p>
       It is true that, in the Bible, verses like Heb 6:19 make refference<br>
to the MHP but in the context of Hebrews can be a little different. In<br>
chapter 9 of Hebrew ( I do not remember exactly the verse ) Paul the <br>
MHP is after the SECOND veil. Logicaly if there is a second veil then<br>
there is a first one (that make separation between th <br>
<p>
<p>
e Holy Place and<br>
the exterior ). I think this is the veil refered by Heb 6:19. If it is <br>
so, the verse speaks about Christ gone into the Holy Place and there is not<br>
contradiction with the usual SDA interpretetion of the 2300 days in Dan 8:14.<br>
<p>
                                          Your brother in Christ<br>
<p>
                                             Alfonso Zerwekh<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
