<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;On Aug 11, Bill Sands, Jr. wrote a number of things, including:</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;Something marvellous did happen in 1844 . Exactly what did</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;happen is still open to study. The major thing which happened</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;as far as I am concerned is that the opening of the spiritual</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;eyes to see that Earth is not the center of the universe,</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;and that there is a heavenly sanctuary in which God is,</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;and Jesus is there as my intermediary. This is a major</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt;shift in focus, and opens the eyes to eternal verities.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;This leaves me with a big question.  An intermediary is one who settles</i><br>
<i>&gt;disputes, reconciles disagreements.  If this is Jesus' job, He is working </i><br>
<i>&gt;for at least two parties.  Who are these two (or more) parties?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;-----</i><br>
<i>&gt;Craig R. Kinzer</i><br>
<i>&gt;craig@polaris.lasierra.edu</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
    One part is God (the Father) and the other is the man (we). It is clear when<br>
we see the consequences of our sin..<br>
<p>
<p>
Jackson Gois<br>
jackgois@cat.cce.usp.br<br>
