<title>Aug2_1994: Re: Re[2]: requirements for a new pastor</title>
<h1>Re: Re[2]: requirements for a new pastor</h1>
Carlyle B. Edwards (<i>carlyle@iquest.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 18 Aug 1994 17:12:42 -0500 (CDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#120">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#120">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#120">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#120">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0121.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "More on Gay Rights"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0119.html">Bruce Holm: "Re: Sabbath School"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In-Reply-&gt;To:  &lt;10AUG94.25750408.0070.MUSIC@MUSICB.MCGILL.CA&gt; from "JAYNE ROP" at Aug 10, 94 11:50:34 pm<br>
<p>
JR wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Has it reached the point where each church gets to</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; choose who they want as a pastor???</i><br>
<p>
So far, only certain churches are able to do this, however it may not <br>
be a bad idea if more churches were able to do this.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I don't understand, but I thought pastors serve where</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; the Spirit leads them, not where they are wanted. </i><br>
<p>
By phrasing this sentence this way, it sounds like you are strongly impliing<br>
that the Spirit can only lead the conference committee/administrators who<br>
"send" the pastors to their churches and CAN'T lead a local churches search<br>
committee members.    <br>
<p>
I think that far too often when the conference places a call for a pastor,<br>
or when they decide to swap a few pastors around from church to church;<br>
it may be done based on other factors other than purely the Lord's or Spirit's<br>
leading.  Especially those conferences who have a strong history of moving<br>
pastor's around on a fairly regular basis every 4-5 years or sometimes less. <br>
<p>
The early church in the New Testament allowed churches a certain degree<br>
of latitude in placing their calls for pastors, etc.  I feel that it may<br>
not be such a bad idea for today as well.<br>
<p>
I firmly believe that the Lord and the Spirit can lead a local churches <br>
decision for a specific pastor or list of pastors just as easily and as<br>
effectually as They can lead a conference administration or committee. <br>
<p>
Carlyle B. Edwards<br>
carlyle@iquest.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
