<!-- body="start" -->
    I just recently saw a program where they showed a medical procedure which<br>
would apply along the lines of this topic.  There's a condition where some<br>
people get a swollen blood vessel in the brain.  Well, there is this man that<br>
the blood vessel was swollen to the size of a golf ball. If that vessel were<br>
to burst, he would die.  Normally the swollen blood vessel is operated on but<br>
that was not possible because of the size.<br>
    A doctor realized that at low temperatures the brain will survive for<br>
some time without oxygen, so he developed a procedure in which the<br>
temperature of the patient is dropped with ice packs and then the heart is<br>
stopped.  The doctor then has up to one hour to operate on the patient<br>
without danger of the blood vesses bursting. Of course this is a procedure<br>
that is used as a last resort. <br>
    They showed tha patient after the operation and he was like a little<br>
child. He had to learn how to talk all over again. But eventually he will<br>
regain his memories and be back to normal.<br>
    I found this amazing.  We are able to stop a persons heart and then<br>
restart it again with minimal consequences to the person.<br>
 <br>
Hector Puig<br>
HectorP2@aol.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
