<title>Aug1_1994: Re: Question about "SDA Reform Movement"?</title>
<h1>Re: Question about "SDA Reform Movement"?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 9 Aug 1994 16:55:03 -0700 (MST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#215">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#215">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#215">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#215">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0216.html">Tony Dyson: "RE: All scripture..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0214.html">94POLLOK@cua.edu: "re: requirements for a new pastor"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; I just received this note from Rich Wales and I am unable to shed any light on</i><br>
<i>&gt; any "Reform Movement" for him.  How about any of you out there?  Also, I am </i><br>
<i>&gt; interested in this information myself, since I've not yet come across this.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Here is Rich's message.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Janet Brown</i><br>
<i>&gt; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;From	CRL::"richw@mks.com" "Rich Wales"  7-AUG-1994 15:49:41.06</i><br>
<i>&gt; Subj:	Question about "SDA Reform Movement"?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; While driving through southeastern Ontario (Niagara peninsula) yester-</i><br>
<i>&gt; day, I noticed a church with a sign reading as follows:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 			Welcome to the</i><br>
<i>&gt; 			CHURCH OF THE</i><br>
<i>&gt; 		    SEVENTH DAY ADVENTIST</i><br>
<i>&gt; 		       Reform Movement</i><br>
<p>
This title is not at all familiar to me.  I have not heard of any "concerned<br>
brethern" (CBs in Oz, which I believe is what George Tasker is thinking),<br>
"historic SDAs", or any such establishing churches with any name other than<br>
the standard "Seventh-day Adventist", no more, no less.  Thus, I would suspect<br>
we're looking at a small off-shoot group here. (FWIW, there are Davidians and<br>
Branch Davidians in Ontario, some near Huntsville, I think.)<br>
<p>
There is a major off-shoot called the "Reformed Seventh-day Adventist" church.<br>
I am aware of congregations in Colorado, California, and Ontario.  A somewhat<br>
simplistic explanation of their origins:  During WWI, there was a major<br>
disagreement in Germany over whether SDA young men should bear arms or not<br>
when drafted into the Kaiser's army.  Absent a "conscientious objectors"-type<br>
arrangement, some US-side SDA leaders (A.G. Daniells, I believe) counseled<br>
that German believers could, in good conscience, go ahead and bear arms.<br>
Given that SDA pioneer leaders in the US (and elsewhere?) recommended strongly<br>
against bearing arms in the military (for certain biblical reasons), certain<br>
German believers felt this (new) position an unconscionable compromise (dare<br>
one say "apostasy"?).  Evidently tempers, personalities, and church politics<br>
got too hot, and a large group walked away.  {This info based upon my recall<br>
of a sermon by my then pastor, Bill Bassham, in late '87/early '88.}<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen ("Canajun, eh?" from Ontario)  Email: fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com
Disclaimer: I do not speak for Motorola Computer Group       Fax: 602-438-3836
"For the transgression of a land many are the princes thereof: but by a man of
 understanding and knowledge the state thereof shall be prolonged." Prov 28:2
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
