<title>Aug1_1994: re: requirements for a new pastor</title>
<h1>re: requirements for a new pastor</h1>
<i>94POLLOK@cua.edu</i><br>
<i>Wed, 10 Aug 1994 17:16:24 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#214">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#214">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#214">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#214">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0215.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Question about "SDA Reform Movement"?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0213.html">94POLLOK@cua.edu: "Re: Requirements for a new pastor"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Well, at our board meeting last night we had quite a long discussion<br>
and many points were raised, but fortunately someone had brought along<br>
a list of the requirements of pastors that the conference normally expects.<br>
On reading through it we found it to be a rather complete list, covering <br>
spiritual life of the pastor, family life, professional growth, ethics,<br>
and many other things.  We found that most of the traits we came up with on <br>
our own as desirable (or undesirable) in a pastor, were covered by <br>
that list.<br>
<p>
We realize, however, that no pastor can fulfill all those traits perfectly.<br>
So we voted to have each member take the list home, and find the ten <br>
qualities on that list most important, and rank them from one to ten,<br>
with the opportunity also to add up to two extra ones that weren't on <br>
the list.  Then we will tally our responses, and from the ten most popular<br>
questions we will frame our interview questions.  We are scheduled to <br>
meet with the conference leadership in two weeks and present our idea of <br>
what we want to them and they will present some ideas of people they think<br>
might be appropriate to fill the position.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
