Bill Sands asks some _very_ good questions,<br>
especially the following:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Who sets the rule? ANd what do we do if we disagree?</i><br>
<p>
And yes, Bill, it *is* much more complex than simply<br>
sola scriptura!<br>
<p>
My relation to the Bible has changed, since reading<br>
some parallel scripture texts of various "same" events.<br>
Passages like 2 Sam 24 and 1 Chronicles 21 ("Who done<br>
it", and more); and Matt 26:34/Luke 22:34; John 13:38<br>
vs. Mark 14:30.  In part my lying lips inquiry from a while<br>
back is because of my praying and questioning the Bible<br>
to explain what it "is" and how I can better understand it's<br>
role and purpose.<br>
<p>
I hope we can get pass the pat statements, into real<br>
discussion and learning here.<br>
<p>
In Jesus,<br>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
