<title>Aug1_1994: 1844 Error? Not in my Bible!</title>
<h1>1844 Error? Not in my Bible!</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 9 Aug 1994 21:00:19 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#219">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#219">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#219">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#219">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0220.html">Raylene Dyson: "SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0218.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "Who is Eating What?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0246.html">Benjamin Siyowi Mapani: "Re:  1844 Error? Not in my Bible!"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
When SDAs start to abandon the 2300 days, I wonder how much<br>
they know about the earthly sanctuary, the heavenly sanctuary,<br>
the book of Hebrews, the day of atonement, the work of the<br>
earthly high priest and the work of the Heavenly High Priest!<br>
<p>
Here we have a straw man dilemma. A false all or nothing argument.<br>
<p>
Take the time to study the related items...<br>
<p>
The high priest went into the most holy place no fewer than<br>
five times in the earthly sanctuary.<br>
<p>
The throne of God has wheels on it...see Daniel!<br>
<p>
The earthly sanctuary is somehow a model in miniature of the<br>
heavenly...see The Torah for a myriad of details about<br>
the sanctuary, the tribes given the role of transporting<br>
the furniture and hardware.<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
sands@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
