Some of our board members have suggested that the idea of <br>
alt.religion.sda as a newsgroup name conveys that we are an alternative <br>
religion.  Another possibility might be alt.religion.christian.sda since there<br>
already is an alt.religion.christian.  What do you folks think of this?<br>
<p>
It's important to note that whatever happens to the newsgroup the mailing <br>
list end of SDAnet will continue<br>
.  I am not sure if distribution under the bit.listserv hiearchy<br>
might also suit our purposes.  I have set it up as internet.listserv.sdanet<br>
at Carnegie Mellon, but if it takes a request at every news site to do that <br>
it would not suit our purposes well.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
