<!-- body="start" -->
Very nice, Fred... And what have I gleaned from this story?<br>
<p>
* Prophets don't necessarily make good pastors.<br>
* Don't hire an evangelist if you want a shepherd.<br>
* Even the greatest pastor can't be everything. (Fortunately he shouldn't<br>
  have to be - the church is packed full of Christians all burning with<br>
  the desire to carry on the Lord's mission, right?)<br>
<p>
<p>
By the way, I remember someone asking whether people ever really believed<br>
that the Conference staffing committees were the voice of God. As far as<br>
I can tell, some certainly did believe it, and some still do. I can <br>
remember my own father saying that it wasn't until he himself sat on some<br>
of these kinds of committees that he started to wonder just how indelible<br>
their pronouncements were.<br>
<p>
	Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
