<title>Aug1_1994: SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?</title>
<h1>SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?</h1>
Raylene Dyson (<i>CHRMD@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Aug 1994 12:48:47 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#220">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#220">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#220">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#220">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0221.html">Mark E. Bishop: "Internet stats (from Internet Info) (fwd)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0219.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "1844 Error? Not in my Bible!"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0247.html">Benjamin Siyowi Mapani: "Re:  SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Benjamin Siyowi Mapani said regarding the Reformed SDAs:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; also because of our dress(dont laugh please). A friend of mine</i><br>
<i>&gt; attended their camp meeting this year, and on one of the</i><br>
<i>&gt; days his wife was dressed in pair of trousers, and at that</i><br>
<i>&gt; he was told that "they have counsel on how to dress" so</i><br>
<i>&gt; that his wife could "improve her dressing standards". Ofcourse</i><br>
<i>&gt; the "elders" there showed him all the counsel by EGW and how</i><br>
<i>&gt; to dress in a pair of trousers. They are pretty serious on</i><br>
<i>&gt; dressing standards.</i><br>
<i>&gt; ...</i><br>
<i>&gt; For example, there are some who believe its not right to</i><br>
<i>&gt; drive on Sabbath, so they walk to church.</i><br>
<p>
	Hmmm. Do I laugh or cry?<br>
<p>
	I'm reminded of Paul's missionary journeys to the Gentiles. He <br>
went to them and told them of Jesus. Many were saved and small communities <br>
of believers were established to live among their towns &amp; demonstrate the<br>
love of Christ to those around them.<br>
	A few concerned people did their own missionary journey behind Paul <br>
and told those communities that they should be circumcized and keep the<br>
Jewish days/feasts etc.<br>
	Paul was not pleased. He told the Gentile believers that if they<br>
were circumcized they would no longer be saved. He told the Jews to stop<br>
making it difficult for the Gentiles to accept Christ.<br>
<p>
	I wonder if I see comparison with such groups as those mentioned<br>
by Ben above and their specific laws and codes.<br>
	In fact I even wonder if the mainstream SDA church is guilty of<br>
some of this - and I'd appreciate your thoughts on this issue.<br>
	When we take a non-Christian and make him/her a SDA, are we not<br>
fettering them with the Sabbath/vegetarianism/other culturally based<br>
behaviours? This "life style" may be a blessing to us just as the Jews<br>
found their identity &amp; fulfillment in their days &amp; laws. To the new<br>
Gentile Christians though, they would so easily lose their freedom in God<br>
by becoming enslaved to these same days/laws (which to them were not<br>
familiar). How many new SDAs become enslaved to our days/laws? I'm finding<br>
this a very disturbing thought.<br>
<p>
Some ideas?<br>
Raylene<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
