<!-- body="start" -->
Bill, you are right here, in implying that when "only it<br>
was required" the high priest went into the MHP.<br>
<p>
There is nothing wrong with 2300 days, nothing wrong with<br>
1844. The problem Adventists have when questioned on this<br>
issue stems from the fact that "they do not understand the<br>
subject themselves that well".<br>
<p>
In antiquity, before there was a sinner, how did the heavenly<br>
temple (sanctuary) function? After Lucifer fell what happened?<br>
<p>
Interesting enough I was aimlessly reading EW and on page 89 or<br>
82, I read the statement that angels have "golden cards(like<br>
your mastercard!!)" which they show to other angels when going<br>
out and in! Now why would such a system be required, going out<br>
and in the gates of heaven, every angel flashes his golden card!<br>
<p>
Then again in Story of redemption, (cant remember the page now)<br>
it says Satan was allowed in heaven as much as  desired (cf Job 1).<br>
Was the golden card system a new one after the cross or not?<br>
<p>
I believe we can harmonise these questions by studying studiously<br>
the book of Hebrews and the related passages in all scripture<br>
especially the Psalms and the five books of Moses.<br>
<p>
There was a change in ministry somewhere along the way.<br>
And melchizedek, the priest of the Most High God, in which<br>
temple was he ministering, since he is a priest who lives<br>
forever...<br>
Have a good day everyone<br>
Ben<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
