<title>Aug1_1994: Re:  SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?</title>
<h1>Re:  SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?</h1>
Benjamin Siyowi Mapani (<i>lole@ariel.ucs.unimelb.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 11 Aug 1994 14:46:06 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#247">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#247">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#247">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#247">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0248.html">Carlyle B. Edwards: "Re: Requirements for a new pastor"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0246.html">Benjamin Siyowi Mapani: "Re:  1844 Error? Not in my Bible!"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0220.html">Raylene Dyson: "SDA Reform &amp; fetters in SDA?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Raylene asked&gt;&gt;How many SDAs become enslaved to our days/laws? i'm<br>
		finding this a very disturbing thought.&lt;&lt;<br>
<p>
I dont know the figure, but many would be near that. We forget that<br>
the law is no use to one who is dead... its function is simply<br>
to preserve whatever life is there (spiritual and physical). I can<br>
relate well to this because I was also enslaved in this type of<br>
donts and dos until I discovered the word GRACE!<br>
<p>
Only when people learn the true gospel, then they can start<br>
understanding the value of the law.  A good example is the<br>
question "what can you and cant you do on the sabbath?"<br>
You can easily have a list of rules, and have complex ifs<br>
and only if and so forth. A person who has appreciated the<br>
sabbath on the other hand will always look forward to the<br>
day with such a thirst that the day will be so short...to<br>
him/her it will be important to gather those blessings<br>
promised on this day than worry about when sunset will occur!<br>
He would rather have a whole year of sabbath...<br>
<p>
In short I find our friends the Reformed SDAs to be<br>
pursuing a very works-related type of life. Especially<br>
with EGW, when one can see know intellectually the fruits,<br>
its tempting to do it yourself and not by faith...<br>
<p>
"For no flesh shall be saved by the deeds of the law"<br>
Ben<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
