On Thu, 11 Aug 1994, Benjamin Siyowi Mapani wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Interesting enough I was aimlessly reading EW and on page 89 or</i><br>
<i>&gt; 82, I read the statement that angels have "golden cards(like</i><br>
<i>&gt; your mastercard!!)" which they show to other angels when going</i><br>
<i>&gt; out and in! Now why would such a system be required, going out</i><br>
<i>&gt; and in the gates of heaven, every angel flashes his golden card!</i><br>
<p>
The correct reference is EW 37, 39.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Then again in Story of redemption, (cant remember the page now)</i><br>
<i>&gt; it says Satan was allowed in heaven as much as  desired (cf Job 1).</i><br>
<i>&gt; Was the golden card system a new one after the cross or not?</i><br>
<p>
I'm not sure, but I think Ben may be referring to the following passage:<br>
<p>
  "Satan would invent means to annoy the heavenly angels and show<br>
   contempt for His authority.  As he could not gain admission<br>
   within the gates of heaven, he would wait just at the entrance,<br>
   to taunt the angels and seek contention with them as they went<br>
   in and out."  (SR 27)<br>
<p>
This passage appears to contradict, or at least modify, Ben's assertion,<br>
however.  I see no contradiction between the passage in SR and the ones<br>
in EW.<br>
<p>
Daniel Crowe<br>
Assistant Professor of Physics<br>
Pacific Union College<br>
dcrowe@puc.edu<br>
