<!-- body="start" -->
On Tue, 9 Aug 1994, Harvey Steck wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;  (main body deleted)</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; P.S. What is "Adventist Today"? Who publishes it?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
I just happen to have a copy of Adventist Today with me today.  <br>
<p>
 From their masthead: "Adventist Today reports on contemporary issues of <br>
importance to Adventist church members.  Following basic principles of <br>
ethics and canons of journalism, this publication strives for fairness, <br>
candor and good taste."    <br>
<p>
I am a charter subscriber and believe that they are achieving their goal.<br>
The current issue is on "Where is Adventist higher education headed?" The<br>
next issue should be verying interesting - Short-term Creationists and<br>
Long-term Creationists. <br>
<p>
It is published bimonthly. Annual subscription, $18 individuals, $12 <br>
students, Add $10 for addresses outside of North America.<br>
<p>
Address: Adventist Today, P.O. Box 1220, Loma Linda, CA 92354-1220<br>
         Voice (909) 824-2780, Fax (909) 824-3880<br>
<p>
Editor: Raymond Cottrell<br>
<p>
I find the articles very well written, it along with Sprecturm published<br>
by Adventest Forum help me spiritually and intellectual.  As the say here <br>
in the Big Easy it gets 5 beans. ( In New Orelans, everything revolves <br>
around food) <br>
 <br>
<p>
Denny Nelson<br>
