I may be a little out of place mentioning this, however;<br>
<p>
In my previous response to this post by Sean Carney, I neglected to also <br>
mention that ASDAL (The Association of Seventh-day Adventist Librarians)<br>
has set up a standing committee who is in the process of investigating<br>
various ways in which to make larger amounts of information and commercially<br>
available databases (both tape load and CD-ROM based) more widely accessible<br>
to all the academic environments at a reduced cost per campus, and other<br>
avenues of increased networking and provision of information access via<br>
the internet, etc.  I am one of five who are serving on that committee.<br>
Harvey Brenneise at Andrews, Gilbert Abella at La Sierra, Joel Lutes at<br>
Pacific Union and Peg Bennet at Southern are the other four.<br>
<p>
Carlyle B. Edwards<br>
carlyle@iquest.com<br>
