<!-- body="start" -->
Well here is a response to the question - this response is<br>
undoubtedly 100% truth, but unfortunately it's not a whole<br>
lot of use.<br>
<p>
Yes, _all_ abortion is sin, in the same sense that all illness,<br>
sadness, pain and death is sin. Without the presence of that<br>
malady we call sin there would be none of the above. I do not<br>
personally know _any_ Christians that are not opposed to<br>
abortion. Even those that favour the pro-choice line are still<br>
very opposed to it. Unfortunately in this bad old world, though,<br>
we are often faced with the choice between a range of awful<br>
things, with no good in sight.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
