I am furious.  I was standing in the checkout line, and happened to<br>
glance over at one of the tabloid rags, with the title "50 foot Jesus<br>
visits UN" or something similar.  It went on how a tourist snapped<br>
this picture that was going to rock the world.  I did not pay it to much<br>
attention, until my wife pointed out that it was the Harry Anderson painting<br>
of Jesus knocking on the UN building.  I was outraged.  Who ever owns the<br>
copyright on that one, should sue the pants off the magazine.  Boy, that<br>
chaps me!<br>
Cheers<br>
Woody<br>
