<title>Aug1_1994: A Sad Day for Adventism...</title>
<h1>A Sad Day for Adventism...</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Aug 1994 01:01:28 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#275">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#275">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#275">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#275">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0276.html">Dan Drazen: "Re: Harry Anderson"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0274.html">DAVESPARKS@delphi.com: "Re: Re:"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The passing of Dr. Hasel in a car crash causes a great sadness<br>
for Adventists. As one who studied for classes taught by <br>
Dr. Hasel, I believe that the Seventh-day Adventist church<br>
has lost a great scholar and thinker.<br>
<p>
This is truly a sad day for Seventh-day Adventism. The whole<br>
Hasel family and Dr. Hasel's "student family" are in our<br>
prayers.<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
sands@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
