<title>Aug1_1994: Re: Is abortion sin? (fwd)</title>
<h1>Re: Is abortion sin? (fwd)</h1>
Clay Spinuzzi (<i>spinuzzi@bach.convex.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 11 Aug 94 9:19:23 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#253">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#253">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#253">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#253">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0254.html">Dan Landrum: "Why a taboo subject?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0252.html">Clay Spinuzzi: "The motorized throne of God"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDA Net said:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; [This is a message on abortion.  I'll send it through, but remind</i><br>
<i>&gt; you all that abortion is officially a taboo topic on SDAnet and I</i><br>
<i>&gt; reserve the right to cut off this discussion at any time.  SCT]</i><br>
<p>
I'll tread carefully on this, Steve. Feel free not to post this if<br>
you want.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; &gt; I have been wondering at what stage of fetal development is abortion sin?</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Do we have a theological basis for our stand?</i><br>
<p>
The question is when the fetus becomes a human being. If you check<br>
out discussions on newsgroups such as talk.abortion, most abortion<br>
proponents believe that the fetus does not become a person until it<br>
has brainwaves approaching the complexity of (born) human brainwaves.<br>
<p>
The problem with this approach is that we as Christians realize that<br>
a person is not merely a mind. We also have a spirit. We can assume<br>
that when the spirit enters the body, the fetus becomes a person,<br>
theologically speaking.<br>
<p>
When does the spirit enter the body? Or is it there at the moment the<br>
egg is fertilized? I don't think there's any way to tell. In the<br>
absence of any evidence one way or the other, I choose to err on the<br>
side of caution and oppose abortion in all instances.<br>
<p>
However, I can't condemn others as evil for thinking that the fetus <br>
becomes a person at a much later date. Actually, I hope they're right.<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
Clay Spinuzzi    Until Aug. 12:  spinuzzi@bach.convex.com
		 Aug. 12-18:     incommunicado
		 After Aug. 18:  (probably) spinuzzi@iastate.edu
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
