<title>Aug1_1994: Eugenics/Abortion &lt;RE: Is abortion sin? (fwd)&gt;</title>
<h1>Eugenics/Abortion &lt;RE: Is abortion sin? (fwd)&gt;</h1>
Marcus Stringer (<i>marcuss@microsoft.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Aug 94 10:05:18 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#283">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#283">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#283">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#283">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0284.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0282.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: Choosing pastors"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Interestingly enough, I was flipping though the TV channels<br>
yesterday and saw a program on Public TV about Eugenics<br>
and the science of genetics.<br>
<p>
The program covered a variety of issues.  Yet particularly<br>
interesting to me was an account of a Mediterranean society<br>
in Europe that has a genetic disease that is hereditary<br>
(showing up in 1:10 of the population).  I forget the name of<br>
the disease, but the medical and religions community<br>
(at least the Catholic church _there_) support using abortion to<br>
"prevent" the continuation of the disease in society.<br>
The disease normally killed the person in childhood, now,<br>
through advanced medicine they are able to treat them<br>
but the result is a larger and larger cost to the "state" since<br>
more ill kids are living longer while new ones continue to be<br>
born, and there is no known cure.<br>
<p>
Of course I have no answers to impose on others just<br>
relaying reality that some people live in, and that I have not<br>
experienced personally - yet.<br>
<p>
What I saw was episode #104 "Conceiving the Future" in a<br>
larger series called "Medicine At The Crossroads" and is<br>
produced by WNET in (New York) and BBS - British Broadcasting<br>
Service.  It's distributed by PBS.  You can call WNET for more<br>
information: (212) 560-2000.<br>
<p>
Marcus<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0284.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0282.html">Harvey Brenneise: "Re: Choosing pastors"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
