<title>Aug1_1994: Re: Is abortion sin?</title>
<h1>Re: Is abortion sin?</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@quad4.phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Aug 1994 11:19:30 -0700 (MST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#284">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#284">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#284">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#284">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0285.html">SDA Net: "Abortion discussion"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0283.html">Marcus Stringer: "Eugenics/Abortion &lt;RE: Is abortion sin? (fwd)&gt;"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In-Reply-&gt;To: &lt;9408102143.AA08046@edmund&gt; from "SDA Net" at Aug 10, 94 05:43:00 pm<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; &gt;From: Mr Emil Gentry Fernando &lt;efernand@HK.Super.NET&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt;Subject: Is abortion sin?</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I have been wondering at what stage of fetal development is abortion sin?</i><br>
<i>&gt; Do we have a theological basis for our stand?</i><br>
<p>
Here are some of the Bible texts upon which I base my position: Exo 20:13,<br>
Psa 139:13-16, Job 31:15, Deu 7:13, Psa 127:3, Isa 44:24, 49:1,5, Jer 1:5,<br>
1 Cor 6:19,20, Acts 17:28, Psa 100:3.  Since I believe it is God who forms<br>
us, I believe we can properly apply Mar 10:9 to this situation as well.<br>
<p>
I am reminded of an experience related by Mark Finley.  He was making some<br>
travel plans at a travel agency (while he was based in Europe).  As he and<br>
the female travel agent were chatting back and forth it came out that Mark<br>
was a Christian pastor.  The agent paused and a pained look came over her<br>
face.  In a voice that betrayed the anguish and confusion in her soul, she<br>
asked, "Do you believe it's a sin to have an abortion?"<br>
<p>
Mark tho't a moment and then asked (very wisely, IMHO), "Are you asking me<br>
because you are thinking of having an abortion? Or because you have had an<br>
abortion?"<br>
<p>
In tears, she poured out how she had met an American businessman on extended<br>
assignment in Europe.  They started living together and sometime thereafter<br>
she found she was pregnant.  She was delighted and hoped he would marry her.<br>
He was aghast and insisted she have an abortion.  Under pressure and fear<br>
of losing him, of whom she'd grown fond, she went thru with the abortion.<br>
But now she was burdened with guilt.<br>
<p>
Mark was able to share with her God's great love for sinners (Rom 5:8), God's<br>
promises to forgive us when we repent (1 Joh 1:9), and that there is no sin<br>
so great (1 Joh 3:20) that God would turn away from the penitent (John 6:37).<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen ("Canajun, eh?" from Ontario)  Email: fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com
Disclaimer: I do not speak for Motorola Computer Group       Fax: 602-438-3836
"For the transgression of a land many are the princes thereof: but by a man of
 understanding and knowledge the state thereof shall be prolonged." Prov 28:2
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
