Hi, Friends,<br>
<p>
First, thanx to everyone for your prayers for my friend,<br>
Reds.  He is still in Fairfax Hospital.  The doctors have<br>
determined that he is having difficulties due to his<br>
diverticulitis.  Reds has not eaten solid food since Monday.<br>
He's being fed intravenously.  I spoke to him today and<br>
yesterday, and will be visiting him tonight.  He says<br>
he feels better, but he has to have pain killers in order<br>
to get real sleep.<br>
<p>
Even though he is in pain, Reds is still making jokes.<br>
We sent him a beautiful dish garden with a card that<br>
said, "Do not eat this=ADthis is not a salad!"  He got a<br>
kick out of that.<br>
<p>
I'm going to print out the responses to my prayer request<br>
and take them to the hospital with me tonight.<br>
<p>
Thanx again!<br>
<p>
God is merciful!<br>
<p>
Cori Bradford<br>
cbradfor@ida.org<br>
Alexandria, Virginia<br>
