A few more details on the Harry Anderson painting which was used on <br>
the front of the Weekly World News (which BTW is biweekly, not weekly).<br>
The headline mentioned a 500-foot Jesus.<br>
Then they used an actual photograph of the UN Building, and took <br>
the picture of Jesus from the Harry Anderson painting (which most <br>
commonly appears on the front cover of Steps To Christ) and superimposed<br>
it on the photo, reversing the image in the process.  <br>
About 1/2 hour work for Adobe Photoshop.  <br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
