<title>Aug1_1994: Abortion discussion</title>
<h1>Abortion discussion</h1>
SDA Net (<i>sdanet@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 12 Aug 1994 17:31:38 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#285">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#285">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#285">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#285">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0284.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Discussion on abortion is something I always try to be careful about, not <br>
only because its hard to discuss rationally, but I myself often get into<br>
trouble for the things I say about it.  <br>
<p>
I recall a forum sesion in Pittsburgh with the precursor of what is now<br>
their chapter of the Association of Adventist Forums.  I was the leader at <br>
the time and had scheduled one of the health-care professionals who was a <br>
member of our church to talk about abortion and the choices that health<br>
care professionals face on this.<br>
<p>
I only found out later that we had a visitor from Indiana that day who was a <br>
member of some flavor of fundamentalist Baptist church and had been <br>
involved in Operation Rescue.  He withdrew from the discussion early on<br>
and did not cause a scene, to his credit.  But he was quite upset that<br>
some of the pro-choice views that were expressed that afternoon were <br>
expressed, and I doubt he will darken the door of an SDA church again anytime<br>
soon.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0284.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
