</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; &gt; Subject: Is abortion sin?</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; I have been wondering at what stage of fetal development is abortion sin?</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; Do we have a theological basis for our stand?</i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; God bless, Emil  </i><br>
<i>&gt; &gt; =============================  </i><br>
 Sometime back I wrote to Biblical Research at GC for an answer to <br>
this question. I wanted a clear No or Yes answer. I got neither. <br>
Unfortunately I cannot locate the document they sent me which <br>
showed the official stand of the church. But it went like this:<br>
Life is sacred and no one should take it away. Abortion is <br>
unacceptable. Then it goes thru some reasoning and finally <br>
gives exceptions, such as cases of rape or mothers health in danger. <br>
I really need to check the document for details. But for sure this <br>
document did not say unequivocally that abortion is sin, period. <br>
As for whether it is sin, I think another question needs to be <br>
answered: when does life begin? In other words is it murder to <br>
destroy a fertilized egg (foetus)? Scientific evidence exist that <br>
indicate life begins after fertilization.<br>
<p>
 If not, when does it begin?<br>
 <br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
    arap-Ng'apng'ap<br>
    serem@agreng.lan.mcgill.ca<br>
