<title>Aug1_1994: 1844  (*^&amp;$%^$&amp;$^)</title>
<h1>1844  (*^&amp;$%^$&amp;$^)</h1>
Bill Sands Jr. (<i>sands@andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Aug 1994 18:19:02 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#234">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#234">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#234">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#234">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0235.html">SEREM VINCENT: "Re: Is abortion sin?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0233.html">Dan Crowe: "RE: The Bible and (Which) Bible Only???"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
If NOTHING happened in 1844, where does that leave the<br>
SDA believer? Are we deceived? Are we disappointed?<br>
How do we explain the significant spiritual developments<br>
of that time period? <br>
<p>
The main benefit from 1844 as I see it is the focus on the<br>
sanctuary on earth as a pattern or model of the sanctuary in<br>
heaven. I do not believe that SDA scholars or scholars who<br>
pooh-pooh the significance of the 2300 days have a thorough<br>
enough grasp of the heavenly sanctuary's rituals, let alone<br>
understanding of all the earthly sanctuary's rituals.<br>
<p>
To trace the movements of the earthly High Priest's<br>
on the day of atonement is a major study. To apply this<br>
information to the Heavenly Sanctuary is another study<br>
for which the book of Hebrews is but a start.<br>
<p>
Something marvellous did happen in 1844 . Exactly what did<br>
happen is still open to study. The major thing which happened<br>
as far as I am concerned is that the opening of the spiritual<br>
eyes to see that Earth is not the center of the universe,<br>
and that there is a heavenly sanctuary in which God is,<br>
and Jesus is there as my intermediary. This is a major<br>
shift in focus, and opens the eyes to eternal verities.<br>
<p>
What do you think of that?<br>
<p>
Bill Sands, Jr.<br>
sands@andrews.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
