<title>Aug1_1994: RE: The Bible and (Which) Bible Only???</title>
<h1>RE: The Bible and (Which) Bible Only???</h1>
Dan Crowe (<i>dcrowe@puc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 10 Aug 1994 14:49:07 -0700 (PDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#233">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#233">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#233">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#233">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0234.html">Bill Sands Jr.: "1844  (*^&amp;$%^$&amp;$^)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0232.html">Cori Bradford: "What works for teens?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
On Tue, 9 Aug 1994, Marcus Stringer wrote:<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; My relation to the Bible has changed, since reading</i><br>
<i>&gt; some parallel scripture texts of various "same" events.</i><br>
<i>&gt; Passages like 2 Sam 24 and 1 Chronicles 21 ("Who done</i><br>
<i>&gt; it", and more);</i><br>
<p>
_The_Seventh-day_Adventist_Bible_Commentary_ (R&amp;H, 1954), in its<br>
discussion of 2 Samuel 24:1, suggests that "God is said to do that<br>
which He does not prevent (see PP 728,739)."  (2BC 710)<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; and Matt 26:34/Luke 22:34; John 13:38 vs. Mark 14:30.</i><br>
<p>
The NIV contains footnotes that explain the apparent discrepancy.<br>
The relevant passages are reproduced below with the footnotes<br>
inserted in square brackets at the appropriate places:<br>
<p>
  "'I tell you the truth,' Jesus answered, 'today--yes, tonight--<br>
   before the rooster crows twice [Some early manuscripts do not<br>
   have 'twice'] you yourself will disown me three times.'"<br>
                                            (Mark 14:30, NIV)<br>
<p>
  "But he denied it.  'I don't know or understand what you're<br>
   talking about," he said, and went out into the entryway<br>
   [Some early manuscripts 'entryway and the rooster crowed'].<br>
                                            (Mark 14:68, NIV)<br>
<p>
  "Immediately the rooster crowed the second time.  [Some early<br>
   manuscripts do not have 'the second time'.]  Then Peter<br>
   remembered the word Jesus had spoken to him: 'Before the<br>
   rooster crows twice [Some early manuscripts do not have<br>
   'twice'.] you will disown me three times.'  And he broke<br>
   down and wept."  (Mark 14:72, NIV)<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I hope we can get pass the pat statements, into real</i><br>
<i>&gt; discussion and learning here.</i><br>
<p>
I hope that this response qualifies.  |-)<br>
<p>
Daniel Crowe<br>
Assistant Professor of Physics<br>
Pacific Union College<br>
dcrowe@puc.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
