<title>Aug1_1994: What works for teens?</title>
<h1>What works for teens?</h1>
Cori Bradford (<i>cbradfor@ida.org</i>)<br>
<i>10 Aug 1994 17:45:49 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#232">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#232">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#232">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#232">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0233.html">Dan Crowe: "RE: The Bible and (Which) Bible Only???"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0231.html">MELDOUGLASS@delphi.com: "Re: Pastors &amp; Purgatory"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi, friends!<br>
<p>
This post is for folks who have worked, or are presently<br>
working, with church-sponsored programs for teenagers.<br>
I am particularly interested in how your group reached<br>
other teenagers in your community, not only the teens<br>
who were currently attending your church.<br>
<p>
If you are the parent of a teenager, when you get the<br>
opportunity, please ask your teen about some of their<br>
likes and dislikes.<br>
<p>
Praise God, a couple of my church family members have<br>
committed to working with me on this project, so now<br>
I'm on a mission.<br>
<p>
Have a nice evening in the Lord!<br>
<p>
Cori Bradford<br>
cbradfor@ida.org<br>
Alexandria, Virginia<br>
<p>
P.S.  Rashid has agreed to go to church with me again,<br>
this coming Sabbath.  The Lord is wonderful!<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
