<html><head><title> Tax Initiatives--8/8/95 -- ATR</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><h3>TAX INITIATIVES  8/8/95</h3></center>
<HR>

<a href="/atr/1.html">ATR Home</a><P>
<a name="Index"<P></a>
<center><b>States with tax initiative measures</b><br>
<a href="#Alaska">Alaska</a>
 | <a href="#Arizona">Arizona</a>
 | <a href="#Arkansas">Arkansas</a>
 | <a href="#California">California</a>
 | <a href="#Colorado">Colorado</a>
 | <a href="#Florida">Florida</a>
 | <a href="#Idaho">Idaho</a>
 | <a href="#Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a>
 | <a href="#Michigan">Michigan</a>
 | <a href="#Missouri">Missouri</a>
 | <a href="#Nevada">Nevada</a>
 | <a href="#Ohio">Ohio</a>
 | <a href="#Oregon">Oregon</a>
 | <a href="#Utah">Utah</a>
 | <a href="#Washington">Washington</a>
<P>
<hr size="6"></center>
<pre>
<font size="+3"><B>STATE	LEGISLATION</b></font> 
<hr size="6">
<a name="Alaska"></a>ALASKA		-Taxing Oil and Gas Companies
<hr>
<a name="Arkansas"></a>ARKANSAS	-Voter approval of all taxes or increases, 
		repeals	certain taxes, exemption from 
		certain types of  insurance
<hr>
<a name="Arizona"></a>ARIZONA		-Voter approval of tax for baseball stadium
<hr>
<a name="California"></a>CALIFORNIA	-People's Tax Reform Initiative
			-Replace current tax code with 2.5%
			Flat Tax
		-2/3rds  vote approval for tax increases 
		-Tax limit measure to strengthen Prop. 13
			voter approval of taxes	and closure 
			of fiscal loopholes for raising taxes
<hr>
<a name="Colorado"></a>COLORADO	-Non-profit tax exemption proposal  
<hr>
<a name="Florida"></a>FLORIDA		-Florida Tax Cap Committee
			-Revenue  limitation,  tax limitation
			(voter approval of new taxes/fees)
		-Just one tax
		-Voter approval of city taxes
<hr>
<a name="Idaho"></a>IDAHO		-School tax credits
<hr>
<a name="Massachusetts"></a>MASSACHUSETTS	-Free the Pike-User fee's removed on toll road
		-Repeal excise tax on registered motor vehicles
		-Sales tax reform
		-Repeal sales tax on telecommunications and 
			consumer electronics
<hr>
<a name="Michigan"></a>MICHIGAN	-Voter approval for any tax increase
		-Voter approval of taxes and legislative pay 
			raises
		-Voter approval of any tax
<hr>
<a name="Missouri"></a>MISSOURI	-Re-authorization of the parks and soils 
			sales tax
<hr>
<a name="Nevada"></a>NEVADA		-Gibbons Tax Restraint Initiative
			-Taxes must be approved by a 2/3rds
			vote of  both houses of legislature
<hr>
<a name="Ohio"></a>OHIO		-3/5 vote of house and senate to raise taxes
		-Supermajority for tax increases & block 
			unfunded mandates
<hr>
<a name="Oregon"></a>OREGON		-Anti-voter approved taxes
		-vote of 2/3rds to pass legislation
		-expanding bottle bill
<hr>
<a name="Utah"></a>UTAH		-Remove sales tax from food
<hr>
<a name="Washington"></a>WASHINGTON	-Measure relating to tax increases
