<HTML>
<HEAD><title>Grover's Page -- ATR</title></HEAD>
<BODY Bgcolor=#FFFFFF><CENTER><a href="/atr/bar4.map"><img src="/atr/bar4.gif" ismap border="0"></a>  </CENTER>
<BOLD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3>GROVER G. NORQUIST</BOLD></CENTER></FONT><p>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="atragnor.gif">
	<BOLD>We all know that federal, state, and local governments have grown much too large, too intrusive, and too costly. But you may not fully realize just how costly government  has become.<P>
	The average taxpayer works from January 1 to May 6 just to pay taxes. That's every penny we earn for over four months. Only then can we begin to keep money we earn to buy housing, food, and clothing to take care of our families.</BOLD><P>
	Direct taxes are only part of the problem.  When we add the regulatory burden on American businesses and individuals, the average American works until July 9 to pay both taxes and the true cost of regulations. <P>
	This is out of hand. Together, we can begin to turn America around and restore individual liberty, accountability, and responsibility.<P>
	On Nov. 8, 1994, exactly five years after the Berlin Wall fell, Americans rejected the costly failures that 40 years of extreme liberal policies in Congress had brought us.<P>
	Americans who had committed so much time, energy, and treasure to defeating Soviet imperialism, could now focus on repairing the damage that Imperial Washington has caused in their lives.  We have only just begun to turn the corner.<P>
	Americans for Tax Reform (ATR) works in cooperation with hundreds of state and local taxpayer groups to fight against any and all tax hikes.<P>
	Every year ATR asks all Members of Congress and candidates to sign the Taxpayer Protection Pledge committing lawmakers to oppose any and all income tax increases.  To date, 196 members of the House of Representatives and 30 members of the Senate have signed ATR's pledge.  Of the candidates for president:  Bob Dole, Phil Gramm, Robert Dornan, Lamar Alexander, Pat Buchanan,  Alan Keyes, and Arlen Specter have taken the pledge.  Bill Clinton, and Richard Lugar have refused to make this commitment to taxpayers.	ATR also works with state and local taxpayer groups to ask candidates for state legislatures to sign a State Taxpayer Protection Pledge against tax hikes.<P>
	Our goal is to stop tax increases.  This will force politicians to focus on cutting spending, eliminating programs, and returning resources to taxpayers who earn them.<P>
	This is a containment strategy against big government.  Just as the Soviet Empire was told it could not grow by conquest, so too must big government first be told it cannot grow unrestrained as a parasite on the economy.  It must be rolled back and once again become the people's servant, rather than a master.<P>
	 ATR looks forward to working with every taxpayer and every interested group to restrain oversized government.  Just as importantly, our affiliate, the Americans for Tax Reform Foundation (ATRF),  sponsors research and education projects which help inform Americans about the true cost of government. <P>
	 As taxpayer advocate Howard Jarvis wrote, "Death and taxes may be inevitable, but being taxed to death is not"<P>
	As publisher, I take pride in welcoming you to this first issue of our new ATRF newspaper.   American Tax Reformer is dedicated to informing you about current issues in the tax reform movement.  Our goal is to distribute American Tax Reformer to an increasingly wider audience in the general public through libraries, universities, gift subscriptions for students, and other means.  In this way, we hope to fulfill the primary educational mission of the Americans for Tax Reform Foundation.  We hope you like this issue and that you will write us with your comments.<P>

<ADDRESS>Grover G. Norquist is President of both the Americans for Tax Reform Foundation and Americans for Tax Reform.</ADDRESS>
<P>
