<blockquote>
<center><h3>Today@MRC</h3>
<b> Sunday, February 09 1997
 </b>
</center>
<ul>
<font face="arial">

MRC launches its $2.8 million <a href="/mrc/reality">Media Reality Check '96 Campaign</a>.  Find out how you can get involved.<p>

Did the media elect Bill Clinton in 1992?  Will they try to do it again?  Order MRC's new book <a href="/mrc/oldwelcome.html">Pattern of Deception: The Media's Role in the Clinton Presidency</a>.
<P>

Prime Time Television: Do you know what your children are watching?  You'll be amazed.  Read our special report on the <a href="/mrc/entertainment">decline of the family hour</a>.

<P>

Have the media reported on Whitewater accurately (or at all)?  Read our latest study, <a href="/mrc/news">Whitewater: The Story Reporters Love to Hate</a>.

<P>

Read The MRC's final <a href="/mrc/mediawatch/96conve.html">report</a> on the 1996 Democratic and Republican Conventions.

<P>

Limited Time Only -- FREE SIX-MONTH MEMBERSHIP TO THE MRC -- <a href="/mrc/membership">Sign up now</a> and you'll receive our monthly membership newsletter, a "Fight the Liberal Media" survival pack, discounts on all MRC publications, and much much more.

</font>
</ul>
</blockquote>

