<head>
<title>CLINTON'S LAND OF NEW PROMISE' MUST INCLUDE THE
UNBORN</title>
</head>

<body>

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
JANUARY 21, 1997<br>
Contact: Jeff Hollingsworth<br>
(703) 836-8602<p>

<center>
<h2>CLINTON'S LAND OF NEW PROMISE' MUST INCLUDE THE
UNBORN;<br> MAKE ABORTION ON DEMAND A THING OF THE PAST,
ACU SAYS</h2>
</center>

<p>
ALEXANDRIA, VA.--- "In his Inaugural address, President Clinton spoke optimistically of
America as a  land of new promise' as we approach the 21st Century. But if America is to
remain true to its heritage as the land where life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness
are among the blessings of citizenship, it cannot remain the land of broken promises when it
comes to the right to life," said American Conservative Union (ACU) Chairman David A. Keene.
<P>
     "The President claimed during his campaign that he is committed to making abortions
more rare in this country. He went so far as to buy political ad time on Christian radio
stations trying to make his case," Keene said. 
<P>
     "If the President would have us take him at face value, he must start translating words
into deeds, " Keene continued. "That means he should support rather than veto legislation
banning partial-birth abortions - - a practice so macabre that even many pro-abortion
supporters don't endorse it. If his Administration won't propose them, he should at least
support initiatives from Congress providing encouragement and additional incentives for
adoption. He should support private-sector projects and programs providing education and
counseling in support of the right to life and move away from those which push abortion as
the option of first resort.
<P>
<center>MORE. . .</center>
<P>
ACU, Page 2
<P>
     "In his Inaugural address on Monday, the President made unusually frequent references to
children and to future generations who will benefit from this  land of new promise,'" Keene
continued. "The striking irony is that his campaigns enjoyed the active support of the
abortion industry and its allies, and his Administration is the most avowedly pro-abortion
in history. He can't have it both ways. As long as abortion on demand is sanctioned by his
Administration, his lofty rhetoric about brighter days ahead for children and future
generations will ring hollow."
<P>
     On the eve of the twenty-fourth anniversary of the Supreme Court's Roe vs. Wade
decision legalizing abortion, Keene called on Congress and the President to relegate
unrestricted abortion to the history books. 
<P>
     "If the President really wants us to believe he is pro-life, he could publicly reject the
flawed reasoning and faulty science upon which Roe vs. Wade rests and work with the Congress
to craft a human life amendment to the Constitution, " Keene concluded.         
<P>
     ACU, founded in 1964, is the country's oldest grassroots-oriented conservative lobbying
organization. On behalf of its nearly one million members and supporters, it lobbies on a
wide range of issues before the Congress.
<P>
<center>-30-</center>

<P>

1007 Cameron Street, Alexandria, VA 22314<br>
PHONE: (703) 836-8602 FAX: (703) 836-8608<br>
E-Mail: <a href="mailto:info@conservative.org">info@conservative.org</a> WWW: <a href="http://www.conservative.org">http://www.conservative.org</a><p>

[ <a href="/conservative/">ACU Home Page</a> ]
</body>
